title: taffy apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Put mixture into small serving bowl; top with nuts. Serve with apple wedges.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, shortening, salt, egg and 4 cups flour; stir until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise, punch down and pinch off rolls and let rise double and bake.

title: colossal black olives stuffed with pesto-cream filling
directions: Puree all ingredients except olives in a food processor or blender.
Spoon mixture into a pastry bag and pipe into olive cavities.
Chill until serving time.

title: parfait pie for diabetics
directions: Bake pie shell and set aside.
Follow directions for making pudding except use 1 1/2 cups milk rather than two cups.
Put chocolate pudding in pie shell, then mix vanilla pudding also with 1 1/2 cups milk and pour on top of chocolate pudding in pie shell. Put Cool Whip over all and serve.

title: pork chop-potato scallop
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Blend soup, sour cream and water together.
Alternate layers of chops and potatoes (seasoned with salt and pepper).
Top layer should be chops and sauce.
Cover (2-quart casserole dish) with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: oriental-style flank steak
directions: Score steak on both sides.
Pour combined remaining ingredients over steak.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight, turning once.

title: play doe
directions: Mix together and cook for 5 minutes.
Take off stove. Separate into 4 or 5 balls.
Now, add food coloring.
Seal in airtight containers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet and saute mushrooms for 5 minutes; remove and set aside.
Brown meat and stir in broth (reserving 2/3 cup), onion, ketchup and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend reserved broth with the flour; stir into meat.
Add mushrooms and heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Blend ginger ale and sherbet; pour into punch bowl.
Add additional scoops of sherbet and cherries if desired.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: no bake pie
directions: Mix together, adding Cool Whip last.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar (may use 1 cup brown and 1 cup white).
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Combine the flour, oatmeal, baking soda and baking powder.
Blend the dry mixture into the batter.
Stir in corn flakes and peanuts last.
The dough will be very stiff.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides and top with onion slices.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over the browned chops.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Spoon sauce over chops when served.

title: fudge
directions: Cook all together until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball; remove from the fire.
Beat well and pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when nearly cold.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
In a large kettle put large can Pet evaporated milk and 4 1/2 cups sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for exactly 9 minutes.
Stir the whole time.
Pour over ingredients in bowl and stir until all is mixed.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Let set for 3 hours.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in flat pan.
Use only one half cake, split and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cinnamon crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange graham crackers in a single layer with sides touching in bottom of greased 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts evenly over crackers.

title: limeade pie
directions: Mix together; pour in crust and chill in refrigerator.

title: chocolate-peanut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line cookie sheet with parchment paper or leave ungreased.
Cream butter with sugars, eggs and vanilla in large bowl until light.
Beat in baking soda and salt.
Stir in flour to make stiff dough.
Blend in chocolate covered peanuts.

title: stuffed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 1 c water until tender.
Cool chicken slightly, then remove meat from bones.
Arrange chicken in shallow 2 qt. casserole dish.
Combine soup, pimiento, and 2/3 c evaporated milk until milk is absorbed by the stuffing.
Spread over chicken. Sprinkle cheese and parsley over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given; spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.
Yields 9 servings.

title: shrimp delights
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray. Add butter and place over medium-low heat. Add next 4 ingredients. Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes until vegetables are just tender, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp and lemon juice. Cook, uncovered, over medium-high heat 4 to 5 minutes until shrimp are done.
Stir in tomatoes and pepper to taste.
Serve over vermicelli.

title: kolaches
directions: Cream the cream cheese, oleo and salt.
Take the warm milk; dissolve yeast, then mix with first mixture.
Add flour; mix and cover.
Leave in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Roll out and use Solo filling.

title: baked fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients well
and
put
in	a
baking dish. Sprinkle top with rest
of	package
of macaroons, brown sugar and dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: old fashioned blackberry cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add eggs. Add spices and soda to flour and add alternately the flour and buttermilk.
Fold in nuts and blackberries. Great with cream cheese frosting.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
With a pastry blender or 2 table knives, cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Store in airtight, covered containers.
The mixture will keep for some time on a cupboard shelf or for months if stored in refrigerator.
You may use this mix to make hot biscuits: (add 1/3 c. milk for every cup of mix); or for pancakes, waffles, dumplings, etc.
Use as you would a purchased biscuit mix.

title: italian "amore" cake(reduced fat and sugar)
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box.
In a deep bowl, blend until smooth, the Ricotta, eggs, sugar and vanilla and pour the mixture on top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend milk and pudding together until thick.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
When cake is very cold, spread this on top of it.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sprinkle baking soda over diced apples.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add cinnamon, salt and vanilla.

title: japanese ginger dressing
directions: Chop ginger and onion until fine in a food processor.
Add other ingredients and process until blended.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and served chilled.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, seasoning mix and milk together with electric mixer. Form into an oval or circular shape, about 1 1/2-inches thick, in center of serving platter. Surround with lettuce and sprinkle with onions, olives, tomato and cheese. Serve with corn chips for dipping.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil water; add margarine.
Add flour and stir until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until dough follows spoon around the pan.
Put dough into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream well butter, Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar, cream thoroughly.
Add eggs (one at a time), beat 1 minute after each egg. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring (can be added to milk).
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan. Put in cold oven.
Bake a little more than an hour at 300° to 325°.
Wrap cake in Saran Wrap while still warm.
Happy eating.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla together well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients; mix well. Form in balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar.
Put in small cupcake pans.
If using new, nonstick pans, no need to grease, but you may want to spray with vegetable spray if pans are old.

title: beef taco joes
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Add tomato soup and salsa and heat through.
Serve on bread or over rice, top with cheese.

title: cindy's mexican roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese (room temperature); add taco seasoning, chopped and drained chiles and chopped onions.
Spread generous amount on each of the tortillas.
Roll each tortilla separately. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Ready for serving with salsa as a dip. If made ahead of time, be sure to refrigerate.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix sugar, orange juice and orange peel to dissolve.
Next, cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks and flour alternately with buttermilk in which soda has been dissolved.
Add grated peel of 2 oranges, 1 package dates (cut up) and nuts. Last, add beaten egg whites.
Do not overbeat after you fold in the egg whites.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
First 45 minutes at 325°, lower to 300° and bake 45 minutes more.

title: french toast batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Dip bread in batter and fry for a French toast breakfast.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch (loaf) pan.
Blend rest of ingredients until crumbly and pour in pan. Bake at 375° or 350° (glass) until apples are tender and top is brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1/4 pint warm water, 1/2 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons yeast and let rise.
Mix lard, salt and sugar in hot water.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Add flour and mix thoroughly (2 eggs may be added, if desired).
This can be covered with a wet towel and put in refrigerator.
Makes rolls and let rise before baking.
Butter tops of rolls before rising.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm. Makes about 2 dozen 2 x 2-inch squares.
Freezes well and microwave to eat.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine the milk and oatmeal in a bowl and let stand at least 5 minutes. Add the oil and beaten eggs, mixing well. Then stir in the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Bake on a hot griddle (lightly oiled).

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour and add sugar.
Cut in shortening; add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead.
Make as biscuits.
Do not allow to rise before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Drain the fruit well.
Add the eggs, sugar and flour to the fruit juices. Mix well and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Cool.
Add macaroni and chill overnight.
Add the fruit, whipped topping and marshmallows.
May also stir in chopped walnuts or pecans, if desired.

title: venison (deer)
directions: Venison is prepared much the same as beef.
Marinade can be used or a can of Coke.
Let set several hours or overnight. Turn several times or put in a plastic bag and bring liquid over meat by closing bag.
Smoked, baked, barbecued or braised, it's good eating!

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and spices to a cold syrup. Do not heat.
Wash and sterilize 4 pint jars.
Slice onions equally into jars.
Wash and slice cucumbers to fill jars.
Stir syrup well and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Screw on lids. Refrigerate at least 5 days before using.
Will keep in refrigerator at least 9 months.

title: microwave carrot cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and
cinnamon
to
mixture.
Fold in grated carrots and nuts. Pour batter
into
a greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake on High 13 to 15 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: yam cake
directions: Boil yams, mash and let cool.
In large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Beat into first mixture; add nuts and turn into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
This recipe was given to me by Mrs. Aleece Lane in 1989.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in a 9-inch pie shell.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly and pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: jagerocknitzel
directions: Pound pork slices with a meat mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice on both sides (very important).
Heat oil in skillet. Add meat and fry briskly until golden brown on each side.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add flour to remaining oil.
Cook until pale golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken stock and wine and cook gently for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cream, paprika and mushrooms.
Return meat to skillet.
Stir; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with noodles or spaetzle.
There is enough gravy to put over them.
Do not cover.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend biscuit mix, grated cheese, shortening, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cut with fork, mixing to a consistency of coarse crumbs. Add egg yolk and water to form stiff dough.
Knead slightly. Roll into 1/4-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut into narrow strips and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: autumn soup
directions: Bring water to a boil and add carrots, celery and potatoes. When cooked until done, add cooked meat and remaining ingredients. Serve when warm.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except whipped cream.
Let stand 1 hour. Fold in whipped cream and serve.

title: pickle delight
directions: Drain 1 quart pickles.
Cut in strips.
Place pickles back in jar and add sugar, onion, celery seed, vinegar and horseradish. Add 1/2 of sugar to bottom of jar and 1/2 on top of pickles.
Put top on jar and shake jar until all sugar dissolves.
Place in refrigerator and shake jar occasionally.
Twenty-four hours later, they are ready to eat.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar, then add eggs one at a time; mix well.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Edge should be light brown.
Turn off oven.
Let stand in oven with door open for 1 hour.
Chill.
Makes 1 pie.
Top with strawberries or blueberries.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, butter and sugar; mixing well.
Pat even into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, pressing mixture 1/4-inch up sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in a slow cooker or crock-pot. While cheese is melting; brown ground beef in large skillet. Once the cheese has melted, add hamburger and picante sauce.

title: baked quail
directions: Wash quail.
Put in bag with flour that salt and pepper have been added to; shake.
Brown in skillet with butter.
Place browned quail in roasting pan.
Add a pat of butter on top of each quail.
Pour cooking wine over quail.
Add water as needed to pan. Cook at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
This is good served with brown rice.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Put crushed graham crackers in bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan. Mix pudding according to directions and pour over the crackers. Chill. Then slice bananas over the pudding and spread the Cool Whip over bananas. Arrange the sliced strawberries on top of Cool Whip. Then spread the drained pineapple over the strawberries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in oven.
Remove.
In large bowl beat eggs well.
Mix in flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish and level off.
Bake 35 minutes. Remove and let cool 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.
If frozen, defrost and reheat at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix well.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate until served.

title: diabetic applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine
until	fluffy.
Beat egg and sweetener until thick and
lemon
colored.	Add
margarine and mix well. Sift together
all
dry ingredients.
Add to margarine mixture alternately with
applesauce, starting and ending with the dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Add vanilla and blend in raisins and nuts.

title: thin chicken dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
With pastry blender, blend in shortening (or butter).
Beat egg and add enough water to make 2/3 cup of liquid.
Mix all together with a fork.
Knead into a smooth ball.
Divide in half.
Roll as thin as possible with a rolling pin.
Cut in 1-inch squares and drop in hot chicken broth. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; stir in seasonings, tomatoes, soup and rice.
Add 1/2 of olives.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into casserole; top with crisscrossed cheese strips.
Broil until cheese has melted.
Sprinkle with remaining olives.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot (5 quart) for several hours on low to medium.
Can also bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: martha pafford's pound cake
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Alternate flour and eggs.
Will have a stiff batter. Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 300°.

title: croissants(makes 32 rolls)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine yeast and warm water.
Dissolve yeast in water and stir in 1 cup flour, evaporated milk, egg, sugar, 1/2 stick melted butter and salt.
Stir until smooth and set aside.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, egg and cracker crumbs.
Make small patties or balls.
Roll in a small amount of flour and onion.
Fry in a skillet until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash.
Add corn bread.
Mix well.
Add onions, cheese, soup and egg.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, sprayed with Pam, spread pie mix to cover bottom.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover with dry cake mix and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Crush Doritos.
Pour Doritos in a large bowl.
Stir in all the canned ingredients.
(Be sure not to add water to the soup.)
Stir in chicken.
Spread into a large pan and top with slices of Velveeta.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted on top.

title: cherry slush
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until cherries are in bits.
Place in container and freeze.
To serve, spoon into glass and fill with 7-Up.

title: apricot cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes on low speed.
Pour into stem pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
While cake is still hot; pour glaze over top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers. Makes 2 cups.
Takes 10 minutes to make plus chilling.

title: chicken and dumplings(easy and quick)
directions: After boned, remove and put chicken back in three-quart saucepan with chicken cut up in small chunks.
Put tortillas in chicken and broth.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and cool.
Cut up lettuce and tomatoes. Crush taco chips and combine all remaining ingredients together. Add hamburger when cool.
Combine dressing and taco sauce.
Pour over salad just before serving.

title: honey cookies
directions: Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Use donut cutter to cut them out.
Frost.

title: mif's chicken
directions: Melt the butter in 2-quart oblong casserole.
Add rice.
Add chicken breasts.
Add onion soup plus water.
Put in dry seasoning mix from rice box on top.
Dot with cream of chicken soup.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix fat and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: party pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs with 1/3 cup melted butter or margarine and 1/3 cup of sugar until blended.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture. Put rest of crumbs into a 10-inch pie plate and press crumbs evenly into plate, making bottom thicker than sides.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and marinate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Serves 8.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together and form balls (approximately 1 1/2 inches) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lynn's meat loaf
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
topping.
Press
meat mixture into a loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.	Drain off fat, if desired.
Top with Tangy Topping and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch cake pan or dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle 1/2 cup melted oleo over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add macaroni, tomato sauce, water, basil, oregano and garlic salt; mix well.
Layer ground beef mixture and cheese 1/2 at a time in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: orange pumpkin soup
directions: In 3 to 4-quart pan, stir oil, onion, coriander and 1/4 cup water over high heat until liquid evaporates and onion is very limp, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add pumpkin, broth, juice and wine.
Stir to blend; bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cut cheese into 1/2-inch chunks and whirl in blender or processor with about 1 cup soup. Return to soup in pan.
Serve hot or chilled.
Garnish with chives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Stir in crushed pineapple, pecans (about 1 1/4 cups of nuts), green peppers and onion.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil approximately 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat butter with soup until mixed well.
Blend in sour cream, onion and cheese.
Thaw frozen potatoes, then stir in soup mixture.
Place in 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with 2 tablespoons of butter and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili-cheese tortillas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread about 1 tablespoon chilies on each tortilla.
Sprinkle each with 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Roll up tightly.
Place, seam side down, in ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cover with aluminum foil and bake about 15 minutes or until warm.

title: cheese beef spread
directions: Chop corned beef in food processor, then blend all together. Serve on crackers.

title: mogen david beef stew
directions: Brown meat on all sides in fat or oil. Put in Dutch oven and add, Mogen David concord grape wine, tomatoes, onions, salt, pepper, thyme, marjoram, and fresh celery leaves. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Then, add carrots, green peas, and fresh green onions. Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over wide egg noodles.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: pudding delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Beat softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over pudding.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add just enough flour to make a soft dough.
Mix well.
Pour dough into 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan, spreading dough to outer edges of pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350°, testing to not overbake.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Store covered.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers (wear rubber gloves to prepare hot peppers) and blend separately in blender, adding small amount of vinegar.
Mix together sugar and vinegar and add peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and food coloring. Pour into jars and seal.

title: apple-phyllo rolls
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with butter flavor vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until skillet is hot.
Add diced apple; saute 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar to sauteed apple; stir well.
Cook apple mixture an additional 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; let apple mixture cool.

title: pork au vin(pork with wine sauce)
directions: Brown pork in oil in skillet over medium heat. Remove pork. Add onions. Cook and stir until onions are brown.
Remove onions. Add mushrooms. Cook, stirring until lightly browned. Return pork and onions to pan.
Add broth, wine and mustard. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes. Stir in parsley. Remove pork and vegetables.
Stir cornstarch-water mixture into juices.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Pour over pork.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use one orange peeling and peel the other orange.
Put the cranberries, oranges and nuts through food chopper.
Add one or two cups sugar to taste.

title: stir-fry greens and mushrooms
directions: Trim and discard tough stems from mushrooms, rinse and drain. Cut caps into thin strips.
Cut stems or stalks from greens, removing wilted leaves. Slice stem or stalks diagonally into 1/2 inch wide pieces.
Cut leaves crosswise into 1/2 inch wide strips. Wash well and drain.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Mix eggs with Ricotta and spaghetti sauce.
Spread over hot spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over and bake 5 more minutes.

title: enchilada casserole(international cuisine)
directions: Cook and season ground beef.

Place one tablespoon of ground beef in center of tortillas; add teaspoon of sour cream, 1 to 2 tablespoons of enchilada sauce and sprinkle both kinds of cheese. Roll tortilla and place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Repeat process for all tortillas.
Spread sour cream over top of rolled enchiladas; sprinkle remaining ground beef over top; pour all enchilada sauce over tortillas and sprinkle with both kinds of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (or until completely heated through).

title: fancy italian salad
directions: Soak head of lettuce 10 minutes in ice water, then shake off excess water.
Break lettuce in large salad bowl. Add tomatoes, cucumbers, radishes and onion rings.
Pour on dressing.
Serve now or better chilled 1/2 hour, then serve.

title: thunder n' lightning pickles
directions: Peel cukes.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Cut halves into thirds, then in half crosswise.
Put in non-reactive bowl and cover with brine made with ice water and salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: "6 cup salad"
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: italian rolls
directions: If rolls are used, split end of roll about halfway down. Remove as much of the inside of roll as possible.
Spoon in cheese mixture and wrap each in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together well.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or golden brown.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth out the cherry pie filling. Add pineapple on top of that.
Sprinkle sugar over pineapple and add dry cake mix.
Spread to cover fruit.
Pour melted margarine over dry cake mix and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli; bring it to a boil.
When cooked, do not drain; use 2 cups of water as soup base.
Melt cheese and margarine in a large pot.
Keep on low and stir often.
Add milk to
base.
Add mushroom soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Add melted cheese and margarine.
Keep on low and stir often.
Combine with broccoli and garnish with croutons and grated onions.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in greased and lightly floured large tube pan.
Place in cold oven, then set at 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat hollandaise
directions: In electric blender, combine Egg Beaters, lemon juice and red pepper.
Blend on medium speed.
With motor running, remove lid and slowly add hot margarine in fine steady stream.

title: jade punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add the next 3 ingredients; blend well.
Before serving, add champagne or ginger ale, and ice cubes.
(Optional:
Float strawberries on top.)

title: chili egg bake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until the top is light brown and the center is firm.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach leaves into bite-size pieces in a mixing bowl. Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in crock-pot on high.
Cook ground beef and onion together; drain grease.
Mix with melted cheese.
Pour in jalapeno relish and mix well.
Reduce crock-pot to low heat.
If sauce seems to get too thick, add water.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken, onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasonings and green pepper.
Bring to a full boil.
Simmer for about ten minutes, then add rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin cookies(double this)
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining.
With spoon, drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake 1/2 mixture in greased and floured 9
x 13-inch pan at 350° for 5 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat.
Spread over cooled cake mixture. Add pecans and chips.
Pour over rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Cook noodles until tender in large amount of boiling water. Drain; rinse in cold water.
Saute onions and green peppers in oleo.
Stir in one can cream of mushroom soup, milk, pimento and basil.
To layer, place half of noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with half of the sauce, cottage cheese, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers with the other half of each.
Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken pipian breast
directions: Fry chicken in olive oil until golden brown.
Remove from pan. In the same oil, fry onions, garlic, green pepper and coriander. Remove vegetables; drain oil.
Return chicken to pan.
Add some chicken broth and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
In blender or food processor, blend onion, green pepper and garlic with some broth.
Blend in peanut butter and tomato paste to a consistency of gravy.
Add this to the chicken and simmer 10 minutes more.
Serve on white rice.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar with fruit.
Bring to a boil (until fruit softens). Melt stick of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour with milk; mix well.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour fruit on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour filling into pie shell and top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Cream the sugars, shortening and peanut butter. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Add to mixture and beat well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in additional granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 8 minutes. Remove from oven.
Press a milk chocolate candy in center of each warm cookie. Return to oven and bake for 3 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies. Stores well.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Melt in microwave the chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth. Add vanilla. Pour over Crispix and mix together gently. Coat with powdered sugar (use a plastic bag or large container with lid).

title: pork chops parmesan
directions: In heavy frying pan, brown chops on one side.
Place chops uncooked side down in baking pan.
Cook flour, margarine and milk together until thick.
Add eggs, onions and cheese and mix well. Spread batter on each chop and cook at 350 degrees for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: sausage and egg bake
directions: Brown sausage, drain fat.
In a bowl mix together eggs, milk, salt, pepper, and mustard.
In a large greased baking pan, spread bread on bottom of pan.
Layer sausage, then cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in casserole dish or pie shell.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly brown pork chops.
Combine all ingredients and pour over pork chops.
A slice of onion may be placed on top of each chop.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Turn chops (and onion) once during baking.
Bake, uncovered, and turn around occasionally.

title: surprise mashed "potatoes"
directions: Steam or microwave the cauliflower until soft. Puree in a food processor, adding the butter spray and half and half to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

title: yet to be named potatoes
directions: Wash and dice potatoes; do not peel.
Place a sheet of aluminum foil on a cookie sheet (foil should be approximately double the size of the cookie sheet).
Apply a thin layer of butter to the aluminum foil.
Put a layer of potatoes on the cookie sheet.
Sprinkle the layer of potatoes with dried onions, garlic salt, parsley and bacon bits.
Place small pads of butter randomly on potatoes.
Repeat layers until potatoes are gone.
Top last layer with a few strips of uncooked bacon and bacon grease. Wrap potatoes in the aluminum foil and bake at 370° for 1 hour or until done.

title: homemade bologna
directions: Mix with hand; roll in 2 rolls in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in shallow pan at 300°.
Turn one time to brown evenly.
Cool on rack.

title: deviled pimento spread
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple chutney(indian style)
directions: In hot oil, add cumin seed, cinnamon and cloves.
Add pineapple preserves and heat it thoroughly.
Add salt, lemon juice and chili powder.
Cool it and store it in refrigerator.

title: baked onion dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
In large mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Pour mixture into baking dish; bake 45 minutes until top is slightly brown.
Serve hot with buttery round crackers. Makes 6 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; this includes apples. Add eggs, oil and vanilla and blend well. Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool and frost.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Combine hamburger, Worcestershire sauce, onion, catsup, garlic juice, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each patty.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together sour cream, 1 1/2 teaspoons taco seasoning mix, cream cheese and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix well with electric mixer on medium speed.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining taco seasoning mix and fix following directions on package.
Drain on paper towels to make sure all the grease is out of the mixture.
Put on top of cheese mixture.
Dice tomatoes and green peppers and sprinkle on top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place broken graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt together butter, margarine and sugar.
Boil 2 minutes (it is important to use both butter and margarine).
Spoon this mixture over each cracker.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When done, take off the sheet right away.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Put 1 stick butter in deep dish in oven to melt.
Beat together ingredients and mix until batter is smooth.
Pour over melted butter; place one can fruit and juice over batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and add soup and other ingredients.
Put in a cake pan and line Tater Tots on top.
Put in 350° oven and when Tater Tots are brown, cover with shredded cheese.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Shave chocolate into strips.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, chocolate and salt in saucepan.
Stir in milk gradually; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir half the hot mixture into egg yolk; blend egg yolk mixture into hot mixture remaining in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla; pour immediately into pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cover bottom of large frying pan with cooking oil of your choice.
Slice peppers and onions lengthwise and saute on low heat until tender.
Cut sausage links into chunks.
Can be fried in separate pan from peppers and onions or placed on a broiler pan in oven at 350° until done.
Once peppers and onions are tender, add 1 cup of water and let them remain cooking for approximately 5 minutes.
Drain.
This method reserves a lot of the excess oil. Pour tomato sauce into crock-pot or large pot and heat.
Add cooked peppers, onions and sausage.
Makes a great hoagie roll filler or serve with pasta of your choice.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Skin and chop chicken and peppers.
Cover bottom of frying pan with salsa; brown chicken and peppers (no oil).
Simmer on low until chicken is fully cooked.
Heat tortillas by flipping them directly on hot burner.
Fill tortillas with small amounts of chicken and peppers.
Top with both cheeses.
Roll up like a burrito and place on microwave plate.
Sprinkle rest of cheese and salsa over tortillas.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.

title: crabmeat and mushrooms au gratin
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add green and red peppers.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring or tossing occasionally.
Add cream and reserved crabmeat liquid; bring to boiling.
Combine melted butter and flour; blend until smooth.
Stir flour mixture into cream-vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce has thickened and is smooth.
Add crabmeat; simmer for 2 minutes, or until crabmeat is heated through.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Place under preheated broiler.
Broil until cheese is golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add pumpkin, then fold in Cool Whip, cinnamon and ginger.
Chill.
Serve with Gingersnap cookies or Vanilla Wafers.

title: chocolate marshmallow
directions: Mix and cook 15 minutes.
Add oleo.
Pour mixture over chocolate drops, marshmallows and pecans.
Pour into a large flat pan to be cut in squares.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes and leave whole.
Place the potatoes, spices and water into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Be careful not to let them get mushy.

title: sweet northern beans
directions: Drain Northern beans.
Put in a baking dish.
Add sugar, bacon, salt, pepper, seasoned salt and onion.
Use enough pepper to blacken top of mixture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in 10 inch skillet over medium high heat, drain. Stir in sauce mix packet, broccoli, hot water, milk and soup.
Stir in uncooked pasta from package.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat
cream.
Add 1/2 of sugar.
Beat until very stiff. (Can be
beaten
ahead
and stored in refrigerator.) Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add whiskey.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff
and
add
remaining 1/2 of sugar.
Beat very stiff. Fold cream
into
whites, then fold in egg yolks, scraping bottom of bowl with each stroke just until thoroughly mixed.
Serve at once with dash of nutmeg on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Add nuts or cherries, if desired.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Combine all ingredients.
Divide half and chill.
Add 1 large container sour cream.
Add rest jello and chill.

title: glazed pop corn
directions: For a popper of corn each time, use 1/3 c. measure of popcorn - 4 times. in 2 Tbsp. oil if done in electric popper.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Cut margarine in small pats and use at least half of it to line the bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Drain half of the syrup out of the peaches. Pour peaches over margarine. Sprinkle the dry cake mix over margarine. Line the top with small pats of margarine and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, syrup and sugar in heavy saucepan. Stir constantly; bring to good boil.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt chips in double boiler; spread on bars.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to batter alternating with figs and milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 hour or more at 325° in a tube pan.

title: microwave peanutty chocolate drops
directions: In glass mixing bowl, combine baking chips and peanut butter. Microwave on High power 45 seconds.
Stir.
Microwave an additional 45 to 60 seconds to melt chips.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until noodles and peanuts are evenly coated with chocolate mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill.

title: martha pafford's dressing
directions: Put cornbread in baking pan; pour broth over bread.
Mash with potato masher.
Mix all the ingredients with the bread.
If it's stiff, add milk until it becomes juicy.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour or until brown at 350°.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put half the peppers and half the vinegar into blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy until pepper is liquified.
Pour into a saucepan.
Repeat with other remaining peppers and vinegar.
Add the red pepper, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and add pectin.
Boil until it thickens when dropped from spoon, about 20 minutes.
Add a few drops food coloring. Pour into sterilized hot jars and seal.
Yields about 4 half-pints.

title: crispix mix
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven at 350°.
Stir in garlic salt, onion salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Add Crispix cereal, nuts and pretzels plus Cheerios.
Mix until coated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and partially cook frozen broccoli in microwave for 10 minutes; drain.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Bake in oven for 1/2 hour at 350° or place in microwave for 20 minutes on High. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook the potatoes in salted water until tender.
Reserve cooking water.
Saute onion in oil.
Put potatoes, water, onion and seasonings in blender and puree in several batches.
Return to large pot and add warm milk.
Stir continuously, add the cheese, margarine and seasonings.
Heat just until cheese melts, do not boil.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: celeste's corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, sour cream, butter and both cans of corn.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Wash and peel eggplant.
Cut up and put in saucepan with water to cover and a little salt.
Cook until tender.
Drain and mash with potato masher.
Chop small onion fine and small bell pepper fine.
Add to eggplant.
Put enough flour to make thick mixture. In a skillet, put small amount of oil and let heat.
Drop by teaspoon into pan.
Brown on both sides.

title: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together for 2 or 3 minutes.
Beat eggs, not too stiff, and slowly pour the hot syrup into the eggs.
Add vanilla, butter and pecan meats.
Turn into unbaked pie shell. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: pulled georgia cane syrup candy
directions: Boil syrup,
sugar
and
vinegar
to a hard ball stage. Add butter
and
soda;
let
boil
to
crack stage.
Pour into buttered pans.
When
cool
enough to handle, pull until light and porous,
using tips of fingers and thumbs.
Cut into small pieces, using scissors and place on buttered plates to cool.

title: mrs. singleton's spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve soda in the hot water, then combine all ingredients in the order given.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature. Stir in pineapple, onion, green pepper, seasoning salt and 1 cup of pecans. Chill well. Form into 2 balls. Roll in remaining cup of pecans.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, adding extra water if needed.
Yields 6 servings.

title: the chewy chocolate cookie(makes in about 5 minutes)
directions: Cream butter (or oleo) and sugar in large mixing bowl or food processor.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts (if desired).
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft, they puff up during baking and flatten upon cooling.)
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute before removing to wire rack to completely cool.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until fluffy, then add other items and mix together.
Save some of corned beef and place on top of cheese, if desired.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar, then add eggs.
Beat well.
Combine salt and flour in another bowl.
Add soda dissolved in water to buttermilk.
Alternately add to creamed mixture buttermilk and flour mixtures.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian pineapple-banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix well.
Pour wet mixture into dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Tear off 2 1/2 feet of 18-inch foil.
Place meat in center, sprinkle with soup mix, cover with vegetables.
Butter vegetables and sprinkle with salt.
Fold foil over and seal tight to hold in juices.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 450°.
Serves 4.

title: no-bake fudge clusters
directions: Heat the cocoa, sugar, salt, milk and corn syrup to 236°. Remove from heat.
Add remaining 4 ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased sheet and let cool or chill.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid with water; add chilled pineapple juice. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add chilled ginger ale.
Makes one large punch bowl.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Grease casserole.
Put
in the rice and chicken pieces. Sprinkle the onion soup
over
all.
Add the mushroom soup and water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Separate yolks and whites.
In a bowl mix 2 beaten egg yolks, creamed corn, canned milk, oil, shredded cheese and Jiffy corn muffin mix.
Fold in 2 beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish hot chocolate
directions: Blend cocoa and sugar.
Dissolve cornstarch in water in a saucepan.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Stir to a paste-like consistency. Continue stirring over medium heat.
Add milk, a little at a time, continuing to stir with a whisk.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: tuna balls
directions: Shape into 15 (2-inch) balls.
Roll in remaining bread crumbs. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes on each side.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg until blended.
Press mixture in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In small mixing bowl combine 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour over layer in pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cake will not appear done.

title: velveeta cheese peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together Velveeta and margarine in the top of a double boiler.
Add the peanut butter, brown sugar, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Continue stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Pour into 9 X 13 pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, cocoa, salt and sweet milk to a boil for 1 minute.
Stir in other ingredients and mix well.

title: franny's clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven or stockpot.
Crumble bacon and reserve.
Cook onions, celery and garlic in bacon grease for a few minutes only.
Add all ingredients except flour and milk.
Cook for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Mix flour with small amount of milk, gradually add all milk and add to pot.
Add crumbled bacon to top and serve.

title: sesame chicken and asparagus pasta
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Add the linguine and cook at a rolling boil until just tender.
Drain; rinse under cold water.
Drain again and set aside in a large mixing bowl.
Place the garlic, vinegar, brown sugar, peanut butter and soy sauce in a food processor.
Process for 1 minute.
With the motor running, slowly add the sesame and hot chili oils through the feed tube and process until well blended.

title: quiche
directions: Cook pie shells according to package directions.
Mix eggs, heavy cream, salt and pepper; set aside.
Brown onion, drain and put in pie shells.
Add filling.
Shake Parmesan cheese over filling.
Add egg mixture.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: meat and cabbage bake
directions: Put cabbage in bottom of casserole.
Brown meat and put on top.
Pour soup over and bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into small pieces (not thick).
Cook in 2 tablespoons of melted oleo in shallow baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes until well browned.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make golf ball size cookies and place 2 inches apart; bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: lisa's meat loaf
directions: Layer the above ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and flour (mixed together). Add other ingredients and pour into Pyrex dish with melted butter. Bake at 500° for about 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet over low heat.
Add tomatoes and mash up large pieces.
Add rice and salt and simmer until rice is tender.
Taste.

title: sweet peach pickles
directions: Make a syrup of 1 1/2-pints of vinegar and 4 pounds sugar.
Add 1 tablespoon each of cloves, pickling and cinnamon (tie these in a little cheese cloth bag) and boil for about 18 to 20 minutes or until very thick.
Have ready 9 pounds peaches and add to the syrup.
Boil until you can pierce peaches with a straw.
Remove from stove and seal while hot.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions. Drain and rinse with cold water. Place in a large salad bowl. Add the next 12 ingredients. Mix well. In a jar with tight fitting lid, shake oil and lemon juice. Pour over salad and toss. Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight. Stir before serving.

title: clam chowder soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: fried green cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in pan with lid on and cook over low heat, stirring frequently until tender. Serves 6.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Pour 3 cups boiling water over 1 cup rice and let stand about 1/2 hour.

title: dressing
directions: Mix
all
ingredients except margarine.
Melt margarine and add
enough
broth to make the consistency you want.
You can add giblets if you like.
Bake 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown ground beef, set aside after draining.
Saute onion, garlic and bell pepper in olive oil until onions are transparent. Add beef (or turkey) to saute.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice with black beans.

title: walt weldon's rice and beans
directions: Pour 5 cups water over rice and let sit for 25 minutes; drain. Cook limas with 1/4 teaspoon salt in small amount of water just until tender.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Sprinkle cucumber with salt.
Cover and soak 15 minutes. Combine sour cream, vinegar, sugar and dill weed.
Drain cucumber, add dressing.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Slice peaches.
Combine flour, nutmeg, sugar and salt.
Toss peach slices in flour mixture until well coated.
Pour peach mixture into the pie shell.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix well.
Adjust amount of ketchup or horseradish for sharpness of flavor.
Please note that glass bottles of ketchup is thicker than plastic bottle ketchup.

title: easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cut up the chicken into bite size pieces.
In a large saucepan, heat all ingredients over medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, until chicken and noodles are done.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Wash scallops well.
Melt butter and add cracker crumbs and bread crumbs.
Put a layer of crumbs in buttered baking dish. Cover with scallops and half the cream and season; repeat.
Top with any remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger meat in large skillet. Add kidney beans while meat is still cooking, then drain the mixture and cool. In a large serving bowl, toss together all ingredients. Top with dressing and/or taco sauce. Enjoy!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: do-nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl, lightly with spoon. Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: glaze for meat ballsfort morgan, colorado
directions: Mix and pour over meat balls.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper. Coat meat with seasoned flour.
Brown in shortening for 20 to 30 minutes in a Dutch oven.
Add onions and bay leaf; brown 5 minutes longer.
Add 2 3/4 cups water.
Cover tightly and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Add potatoes, carrots, 1 cup water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Cover and cook 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
Slowly add to cooking liquid, stirring constantly, until thick.
Serve garnished with parsley, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls (100 small).
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen in Ziploc bags.

title: pork steak and rice bake
directions: Brown steaks in small amount of fat and set aside.
In same frying pan, brown (saute) rice and 1 medium diced onion.
When browned, pour rice into 3-quart casserole.
Overlap pork shoulder steaks on rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover meat with green pepper and 1 sliced onion.
Pour over all the tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and brown for a few minutes if desired.

title: v-8 juice
directions: Wash and clean tomatoes.
Cook tomatoes and run through colander,
to
7 quarts of juice.
Add
seasonings
to
juice. Heat juice and pour into hot, clean jars.
Process
in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yields 7 quarts.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion into plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with mixer).
Pour into pie plate. Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot cider
directions: Heat in slow cooker to desired taste and temperature.

title: baked apples
directions: Place quartered apples in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, filling dish.
Sprinkle mixture of sugar, cinnamon and flour over the apples, then dot with butter.
Cover apples with water and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn apples and bake 30 minutes longer until tender.
Top with marshmallows and bake an additional 10 minutes or until marshmallows are melted.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: pepsi cola roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Mix Pepsi and mushroom soup together.
Pour over roast and cover. Bake in a 350° oven for several hours or until desired doneness. Great to fix in a slow cooker.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, onion and tomatoes.
Toss with cheese, dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Peel and slice avocado into salad mixture.
Brown ground beef; add drained kidney beans and salt, simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix into cold salad.
Decorate with extra chips, avocado and tomato.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dude's party mix
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in a large plastic bag and tumble until thoroughly mixed.
In a saucepan, mix remaining ingredients. Bring to boil and set aside until warm.
Dribble sauce mixture over cereals while continuing to tumble in the plastic bag.
Continue tumbling until all cereal is coated.
Taste and add more seasoning here to taste.
I add more garlic salt and cayenne.
Bake in small quantities at 225° for 1 hour.
Use shallow broiling pan approximately 2-inches deep and leave space so the mixture can be stirred or shaken frequently to prevent burning.
Save the cereal boxes to store mix.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° until done. Cool.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs and milk with fork until well blended. Dip bread slices in egg mixture. Turn and coat evenly. Place in hot skillet. Reduce heat to medium; cook until lightly brown on both sides.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Blend 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whipped topping.
Put crumbled pretzels over baked sugar and butter.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top. Make jello; add fruit.
Cool until thickened.
Pour over chilled cream cheese mixture.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler until melted.
Mix in noodles and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool; store in airtight container.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix well.
Shape into puffs and deep fry.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in large container.
Stir in crumbs, pecans, coconut, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips together.
Dip each ball in chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in tight container.

title: war cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and boil 5 minutes.
When cold, add flour and soda mixture.
Add egg and bake in 3 layers at 375°.
(If self-rising flour is used, omit soda.)

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter and margarine with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press crumb mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden.
While crust is baking, combine eggs, corn syrup, granulated sugar, salt and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in pecans. Pour filling over hot crust.
Reduce oven temperature to 275°. Bake about 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool in pan on a wire rack before cutting into bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: corn dogs
directions: Will need 8 to 10 wooden skewers.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonful on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bayou jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, saute first 4 ingredients in butter until onion is tender. Stir in ketchup and remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender. Add shrimp; simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour in graham cracker crust. Cool for 1 hour.
Sprinkle crushed peanuts on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook crushed strawberries, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Add few drops red food coloring and 1 tablespoon butter.
Wash and stem whole strawberries.
Put in pie shell.
Pour mixture over strawberries and let set.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: crispy sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in milk and flavoring.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Then stir into sugar mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll thin and cut into desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes or until delicately browned.
Yields 10 dozen cookies.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 4 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable's potato salad
directions: Cook salt and potatoes; set aside.
After cool, mix potatoes, grated carrots, pickles, celery, onion, black pepper and parsley. Add salad dressing.
If desired, add lemon juice and sugar.

title: carol's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Spread on chicken, ribs, etc. before cooking or during last few minutes, as it can burn if cooked too long. Freezes well.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Drain fat if any.
Add gravy and catsup.
Cook on low until desired thickness to serve on buns.

title: veggie squares
directions: Line cookie sheet with crescent rolls, pressing seams together.
Bake according to directions.

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and orange peel in bowl.
Add combined egg, orange juice, margarine, milk and vanilla.
Mix just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups (12) half full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Remove from pan. Serve warm with whipped butter and marmalade.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg. Stir in vanilla. Add flour and baking powder. Roll and cut into shapes on floured board.
Bake until lightly browned at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: potatoes with olives and anchovies
directions: Cut the potatoes into wedges.
Heat the oil in a cast-iron skillet over medium heat.
Add the potatoes; sprinkle with the olives, capers and anchovies.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
When cool, tear into small pieces.
Add cream cheese and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted margarine. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: basil sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in basil, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Keep warm while cooking pasta.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Stir together flours, sugar, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until blended, but slightly lumpy.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter into a lightly greased skillet.
Cook until golden brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and eggs in bowl. Beat until smooth.
Heat 1/2 inch oil to 375° in electric skillet.
Pour 1/4 batter into funnel.
Drizzle in hot oil.
Turn.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape firmly into loaf (8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch); place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: babe ruth or butterfinger cookies
directions: Sift and re-measure flour twice.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth; beat in eggs.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chopped candies.
Drop on foil-lined or greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: choice chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally, for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water. Add 1 cup cold water. That is plenty of water as there is juice in the fruit. Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until not bloody when pressed with a fork. Pour tomato sauce over the top after draining grease off and bake for 10 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar with corn meal, flour, butter, nutmeg, salt and vanilla; add eggs and milk.
Set aside for 1 hour; pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Split one side and scoop out.
To potato pulp scooped out, add butter, a little cream, salt and pepper.
Then beat lightly.
Refill potato shells with this mixture.
Sprinkle cheese, butter and bacon bits on top.
Other items may be added to taste.
Serve hot.

title: egg and sausage souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk, and spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Then pour in milk over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for 1 hour.

title: excellent pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, shortening, salt and soda.
Mix together water, vinegar and egg.
Combine both mixes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Simmer the scallops and shrimp in the wine for 10 minutes. Add the 1/2 cup butter. When melted, drain and save liquid.
Add the clams, crabmeat or lobster, parsley and seafood seasoning. Mix all fish, mushrooms and seasonings together.

title: ham and potato soup
directions: Chop onions.
Cube potatoes.
Slice mushrooms.
Put all ingredients in deep pot.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, covered.

title: apple salad
directions: Toss lettuce and onions.
Crumble in blue cheese.
Chop apples into bite sized pieces and add to salad.
Crush bagel chips in your hand to make bite sized pieces, add to salad immediately before serving to preserve freshness.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Now add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Mix well until batter is smooth.
Pour into greased and floured pan (2 round pans or 1 sheet cake pan).
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Let cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: squash casserole(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place squash and onion in a medium saucepan; cover with water. Add 1 tablespoon salt. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat; simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together.
Beat eggs with milk; gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth. Pour 1/3 to 1/2 cup batter into wide-spout funnel, holding spout closed with fingers.
Allow batter to flow through funnel into hot shortening, moving funnel to form coil patterns.
Drain on absorbent paper; sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve warm. Makes 6 to 9 funnel cakes.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add frozen strawberries, and melt. Add pineapple and bananas.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 9 inch pan. Put it in the fridge for 45 minutes or until set.
Spread on sour cream; add the rest of the mixture on top.
Chill until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash with a fork.
Add cheese and margarine while squash is hot. Add egg and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in cracker crumbs; season with pepper.
Put in shallow pan, greased lightly with margarine, and bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: de walt cooked coleslaw sauce
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise in a small skillet.
Add vinegar and cook over medium heat until it bubbles a bit.
If you'd like, add a tablespoon of celery seed to mixture before cooking.
Add sauce to cabbage, carrot and onion.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: cool dessert
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add melted margarine to flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine bouillon, water, celery and onions; simmer for 20 minutes with lid on. Add frozen vegetables, carrots and potatoes. Cook 30 minutes more.
Stir in soup and Velveeta.
Stir until cheese melts.
Leftover soup is very good on baked potato.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with chicken breasts. Cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
Smooth can of soup over top of the cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over the soup.
Drizzle butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Parmesan cheese, flour and seasoned salt in bag.
Shake potatoes (a few at a time).
Put in pan with melted oleo.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Makes 4 to 5 pie crusts and freezes well.

title: homemade beef sticks
directions: Mix all and let stand 2 days in the refrigerator.
Before baking, make into about 6 tight rolls wrapped in foil.
Bake in pan so sausage can drain as they cook.
Bake 90 minutes at 350°. Will keep weeks stored in the refrigerator.

title: slow baked beef stew
directions: More celery, onions and potatoes may be used.
Put meat and vegetables in casserole.
Do not brown meat.
Blend 2 teaspoons salt, 1 tablespoon sugar and 3 tablespoons Minute tapioca. Sprinkle over meat and add 1 cup tomato juice.
Cover and bake for 4 hours at 250°.
Add 1 cup water.
Use more tapioca to thicken, if necessary.
Do not peek!

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate flour and cola.
Add flavoring last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot dog-a-roni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Heat tomatoes in large saucepan.
(Can substitute jar spaghetti sauce instead of plain tomatoes.)
Season tomatoes with salt, pepper, basil, oregano or Italian seasoning.
Cut hot dogs into 1/2-inch rounds. Add to tomato sauce, heat thoroughly for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni.
Heat and stir 5 more minutes.

title: iced cucumbers
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Pour mixture over vegetables and allow to sit 20 minutes.
Put in plastic container and freeze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil (1 inch) to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until brown, about 2 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: honey fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit.
Mix orange juice, lemon juice, honey and liquid from lite chunks and pour over fruits.
Add nuts.
Stir gently and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until; skin, bone and cut into small pieces. Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle celery seed and onion over top.
Combine soup with 1/2 cup broth; spread over chicken. Combine stuffing mix with remaining broth; spread over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes more.

title: deviled ham sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients until smooth.
Spread on bread, cut into desired shapes and serve.

title: rancho bean bake
directions: Fry meat and onions in pan until meat browns.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes. May be prepared ahead of time and frozen.

title: tossed salad with blue cheese
directions: Blend together all ingredients with the exception of mixed greens. Chill.
Just before serving, pour over crisp mixed greens. Toss.
May add croutons, tomato or avocado.

title: "war cake"
directions: Grease and flour an 8 x 4-inch baking pan. Place the sugar, water, raisins, oil, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in a heavy bottomed saucepan. Mix and bring to a boil. Cook gently for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool until comfortably warm to finger. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Add to cooled sugar mixture, blending well. Fold in nuts; spread evenly in baking pan and bake for 1 hour or until a cake tester comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn onto a rack to cool completely. On special occasions, add cut up candied fruit (pineapple, red cherries). Yield: 1 loaf.

title: chicken-rice hot dish
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter.
Mix soups and broth.
Stir all ingredients together and bake in a shallow baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound each chicken breast with meat tenderizer several times on each side until somewhat flat.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and parsley flakes in bowl.
Dip each breast in mixture and saute in frying pan, using 4 to 6 tablespoons of butter.
Cook for approximately 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Remove when brown.
Add 2 tablespoons more of butter to pan as well as mushrooms and wine.
Cook until sauce thickens, then add chicken.
Simmer 5 minutes, then serve.

title: fullabull's easy boiled custard
directions: Heat sugar and milk in large heavy pan just to boiling.
Blend in blender the eggs, cornstarch, flavoring and pinch of salt. Beat into milk mixture with large spoon and refrigerate.

title: orange cookies with lemon icing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grate and squeeze the rind and juice from the orange and lemon and keep separate (lemon is used for the icing).
Cream sugar and butter.
Add orange juice, orange rind, and egg yolk.
Mix. Stir in baking soda into the sour cream.
Add to mixture.
Combine flour, salt, and baking powder and add to mixture.
Beat the egg white and fold in last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: creole meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix ground beef, rice, onion, bell pepper, salt, thyme and egg.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Blend and shape into loaf.
Place into shallow pan.
Bake 1 hour; pour off fat.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: In large bowl, cut up broccoli heads being careful not to include any stems. Add raisins and sunflower seeds. Crumble bacon into bowl. Add onion and stir. In separate bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, and mayonnaise. Stir well. Pour over ingredients in large mixing bowl. Stir to coat. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: peach easy
directions: First you get the seeds out.
Then pour some sugar in a bowl. Then warm some butter up.
Then we took the butter out of the microwave.
Then we put butter in the bowl, and water and some cornbread stuff, and some milk.
Then stir it all up together and pour it into the pan.
Then let it set for a while.
Then put the cherries in a pot on the stove. Let them boil for a while.
Then we put the cherries in the pan and stick them in the oven.
Cook for 14 hours at 5 degrees.

title: dip for round rye bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate ingredients.
Do not put ingredients in bread until ready to serve.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Blend flour and oil mixture with yeast.
Add buttermilk.
Mix and chill in fridge.
Roll out (thicker than usual).
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This will keep in fridge up to 2 weeks. Chill at least 1 1/2 hours or overnight.
Use tightly covered Tupperware container.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix together margarine and hot water.
Beat and add brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts and zucchini.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch (or 2 smaller pans for less height).
