Spread batter over pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage(fresh)
directions: Wash cabbage well and chop up into small pieces.
Place into large pot with bacon and about 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cover with enough water to cook well.
Serve with fresh onion and corn bread. Yield:
8 servings.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix and beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Stir sugar and sour cream in a 4-quart saucepan.
Cook until candy thermometer reaches 234° (soft ball stage).
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Continue to stir until creamy.
Turn out quickly on a greased baking sheet and separate pieces.
When cooled, candy should become crisp.

title: slow cooker roast beef
directions: Pour the soy sauce and dry onion soup mix into the slow cooker. Mix well. Place chuck roast into slow cooker. Add water until the top 1/2 inch of the roast is not covered. Add freshly ground pepper over the top. Cover and cook on low for 22 hours.

title: steamboat omelette
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 8 slices bread in pan; top with ham and cheese.
Butter remaining bread and place on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add chopped onion and milk.
Pour over the bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, drizzle melted butter over top and sprinkle with the chips.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs, garlic powder, salt and Parmesan cheese. Skin 8 chicken breasts and dip each in 1 stick melted butter. Roll buttered chicken in crumb mixture and place in baking pan. Dot with butter and bake 1 hour at 360°.

title: bacon-vegetable hash
directions: Saute bacon in large skillet and saute over low heat.
When evenly browned and the fat is rendered, drain the bacon on paper towels and set it aside.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of the bacon drippings and discard.
Melt the butter in the pan with the remaining bacon drippings.
Add the potatoes, green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Saute over medium heat until the potatoes are tender, about 20 to 25 minutes, making sure to stir frequently. Add a bit more butter, if necessary, to prevent sticking.
Add the reserved bacon, salt to taste, and plenty of fresh black pepper. Saute for an additional 5 minutes, to allow flavors to blend. Serve warm.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Melt shortening then add milk.
Add milk to yeast, stirring to blend.
Mix with flour as for baking powder biscuits.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter and fold over.
Press down.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 450° oven.

title: homemade hash browns
directions: Chop unpeeled potatoes into small pieces.
(I use my blender.) Melt butter or shortening in skillet.
Pour a layer of potatoes in pan and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cook on medium.
Keep mashed with spatula.
Turn heat up and brown on both sides when fully cooked.

title: oatmeal-chocolate sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in orange juice.
Add combined Quaker Oats and flour, mixing well.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into 2-inch circles.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: spinach artichoke chicken pasta
directions: In a saucepan, mix all ingredients except pasta; cook until well blended.
Stir in pasta.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix milk with ground beef.
Divide into 4 or 5 flat patties 6-inches in diameter.
In the center of each patty, put 1/4 cup stuffing.
Mold meat around stuffing.
Form ball with beef.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste several times.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Pour into greased loaf pans (makes 2 loaves).
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberries with mint
directions: Cap strawberries; rinse and drain.
Combine strawberries, mint, orange juice and orange rind; toss gently.
Sprinkle with sugar; chill at least 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: throw together lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Prepare your favorite sauce.
Mix noodles, salt and pepper and the cheeses (save half the shredded Mozzarella) together.
Layer 1/3 of the sauce and 1/2 the noodles.
Repeat layers and top with remaining sauce and the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rhubarb, sugar and layer of marshmallows in bottom of pan.
Make cake mix by package instructions.
Pour over rhubarb layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When cool, flip cake over.

title: pepperminit rice krispies treat
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat. Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies. Stir until well coated.
Add broken peppermint (break candy using a hammer). Put the candy in plastic bag.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Spread evenly over the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut around edges while warm to avoid sticking.
Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Makes about 24 squares.

title: old fashion fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in slow to moderate oven, 275° to 300°, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare basic biscuits as directed, except after cutting in shortening, stir in cheese.
Bake as directed for basic biscuits.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and onion in a bowl; mix lightly. Add eggs; blend well.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot fat in which fish has been fried. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve spread with butter.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Place rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sugar; dot with 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour 1/2 cup water over all.
Sift together dry ingredients with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut in 1/4 cup margarine until fine crumbs.
Add egg and milk to dry ingredients.
Stir to moisten.
Spread over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet meat balls
directions: Mix beef, eggs, onion, bread crumbs, cornstarch, salt, pepper, ginger, nutmeg and evaporated milk in a large bowl.
Form lightly into about 30 walnut-size balls.
Brown in melted shortening in a large frying pan.
Mix onion soup and water.
Pour over meatballs. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
(I use a small can of milk and a bit of water to make 8 ounces.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, brown sugar and butter. Add vanilla and eggs. Set aside. Mix together the dry ingredients. Add to butter mixture. Then add the chocolate chips and Hershey bars. Stir in the nuts. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brazilian rice
directions: Mix sauce; stir in rice.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a pan of water in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spirit-filled life
directions: Mix all ingredients with joy and faithfulness.
Pour into a saved-by-Christ person.
Bake for a life-time in God's oven at the Spirit's control.

title: tofu spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Combine sauce with pasta and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Combine tofu and cheese in separate bowl and cover pasta mixture with it. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: garlic butter
directions: Put applesauce or other naturally sweet fruit on cookie sheet with
raised sides, about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 300° until thick.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix dressings and seasoning in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: poulet cordon bleu
directions: Dip each breast in eggs.
In center of each breast lay 1 slice of cheese, 1 slice of ham.
Roll all tightly, you may need to secure with a tooth-pick or use string.
Roll "breast roll" in cracker crumbs.
Place in pan.
For 4 breasts halves pour approx. 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup white wine over all.
BON APPETIT.

title: sweet venison or beef jerky
directions: Mix and boil over medium heat; let cool.
Cut meat in lean, thin strips and marinate in refrigerator for at least 24 hours (more time equals more flavor).
With oven on low, bake meat, over a drip tray, on oven rack for several hours until semi-dry.
Also, just before putting meat in oven, coarse black pepper, cayenne or other flavorings can be sprinkled on wet marinated pieces.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in vegetable oil until red disappears.
Add onion, tomatoes, steak sauce, peppers, catsup and parsley. Stir and simmer 30 minutes. Cook macaroni separately and drain.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Put in a large greased baking dish, folding in soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma polly's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for one hour in greased and floured pan.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In greased pan, place chicken pieces and sprinkle with salt, pepper and red pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: dilly green beans
directions: Prepare beans as directed on package. Add remaining ingredients. Toss lightly to blend. Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Chill and mix all but the ginger ale.
Add ginger ale when you start to serve, but hold back enough to add as party progresses. You can also substitute or add frozen lemonade or apple juice.

title: dixie pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat; sprinkle with salt and sage.
Place in baking dish; top with apple rings.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add flour to fat in skillet; blend.
Add water and vinegar and cook until thick.
Add raisins.
Pour over chops.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple and cranberry casserole
directions: Combine sugar, cranberries, apples, dash of salt and lemon juice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix together melted margarine, brown sugar, oatmeal, dash of salt and flour.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
(I use a square 8-inch Pyrex dish.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, then drain.
Place half of Cheez Whiz in bottom of dish, then a layer of squash.
Beat 2 eggs and add salt, pepper, onion and green chiles.
Pour that mixture on squash.
Add layer of mixture and squash, then Cheez Whiz.
Pour that over top, then toast crumbs as final layer.
Cook on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lou's chicken and dressing
directions: To prepare dressing, put chopped eggs in the cornbread that has been crumbled. Saute green onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery in margarine until done; add to cornbread and egg mixture. Add cream of chicken soup; mix. Add 3 qt. chicken broth and season with Tony's seasoning; stir well. Add chicken. Bake in large Magnalite roaster for about 2 hours at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed and drain.
Add onions, celery, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix all together.
Put cracker crumbs on top of casserole and pour 1 stick melted butter all over crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Heat sugar, corn syrup, oleo and salt to simmering over medium-high heat.
Stir constantly, then cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn; coat it well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix these ingredients and spread over pie.
Bake in moderate hot oven--preheated to 375°-for about 35 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler or pies
directions: If frozen berries are used, use 1 cup of flour.

title: fat free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 jumbo muffin pans (3 x 1/2-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda and ginger.
In large bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix shredded carrots, yogurt, egg, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
With spoon, stir flour mixture into carrot mixture just until flour is moistened.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool carrot muffins in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove muffins from pan.
Cool slightly and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 8 large carrot muffins. I also get 3 or 4 normal size muffins in addition.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters with scissors.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon together and divide in half.
Roll each biscuit individually in half of the cinnamon-sugar mixture or toss together a few at a time in a plastic bag.
Put half the biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Take the other half of cinnamon-sugar mixture and melt with butter.
Pour half over the biscuits in the pan.
Put the rest of the biscuits in the pan and pour the rest of the butter mixture over them.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned molasses pie
directions: Place molasses and butter or margarine in saucepan and let come to a boil.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour and sugar and add to eggs.
Add this mixture to molasses mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: meat balls and sauce
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except oil, well, then roll into balls.
Brown in a skillet with oil.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Arrange layers of bread in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
In bowl, combine eggs, milk, undiluted soup, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and garnish with sauteed onions.
Bake in 325° oven until browned.

title: hunk style chicken
directions: Coat chicken in flour and salt.
Brown in oil.
Reduce heat. Add tomatoes, onions, pepper, mushrooms, garlic, bay leaf and parsley.
Cover.
Cook 35 minutes.
Uncover; cook 15 minutes. Remove parsley and bay leaf.

title: nutty cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Meanwhile, in a medium skillet, cook green pepper and garlic in margarine until tender.
Pour over cauliflower; toss.
Stir in pecans.
Serves 4.

title: lo-cal soup
directions: Chop or dice vegetables.
Combine all ingredients in a large kettle and simmer about 1 hour.
Only 30 calories per cup.

title: cream cake
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces.
Beat Dream Whip and cold milk together.
Add sugar and mix.
Beat cream cheese and mix. Place layer of cake pieces (half of cake) and layer of cream mixture; make 4 layers.
Place cherry filling on top (2 cans).

title: simply delicious fudge
directions: Heat milk and chocolate chips until melted.
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate until cool.
Never fails!

title: corn sticks or corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk, well beaten egg and shortening.
Pour into well-greased frying pan or corn stick pan.
Bake in hot oven at 350° for about 25 minutes or until brown.
Can be made with sweet milk, but omit soda.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and pat into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican rice
directions: In blender, blend tomato, onion and garlic until smooth.
Set aside.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook rice until golden, stirring constantly.
Add tomato mixture; cook until all liquid is absorbed, stirring.
Stir in water, bouillon, carrot and salt.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add peas, cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until rice and vegetables are tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Makes 12 accompaniment servings.

title: margot perot's texas sunshine cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto waxed paper. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Mix in orange rind and juice.
Stir in flour mixture until blended.
Mix in pecans. Drop dough in rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets leaving 3 inches between cookies.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.
Remove to wire rack.
Frost with Orange Icing while warm.

title: chocolate mound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add cocoa.
Add eggs.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Put in three 8 or 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: Roll each piece of bread flat with a rolling pin.
Mix together cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Spread mixture on each flat piece of bread.
Roll into rolls.
Dip rolls into margarine and then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl; blend until creamy.
Blend in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually. Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop rounded spoonfuls of dough, 3 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Cool before removing from sheet.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of filling comes out clean.
Cool.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of the soup, beef, crumbs, onion and egg.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat into an 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off 1 tablespoon drippings; reserve.
In a saucepan over medium heat, heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over meat loaf.

title: pumpkin care ring with lemon glaze
directions: Combine cake mix and spices in bowl; add eggs and water as directed on cake mix package, substituting pumpkin for 1/3 cup of the water.
Mix as directed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan and glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon grated lemon rind.
Add just enough cream to make glaze slightly runny.

title: rice dressing
directions: Cook onion in margarine until clear.
Mix all ingredients and put in an 8 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: individual strombolis
directions: Thaw and cut frozen dough.
Roll into pieces about 6 x 6-inches.
Put all the ingredients on half the dough, staying 1/2-inch from the edge; flip plain side of dough over and pinch the outside edges together.
Fry in deep hot oil until golden brown or bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until golden brown.

title: egg bake
directions: Place bread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread. Fry and drain sausage.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover with cheese.
Let set overnight.
Bake in the morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding (powder only) with fruit cocktail, sour cream and 1/2 can coconut.
Let mixture sit overnight.
Mix well. Sprinkle coconut over top and top with nuts and cherries.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water. Cook until it forms a hard ball (260°).
Add 1/2 of the sugar mixture to beaten egg whites, beating while adding mixture.

Cook the remaining mixture a few more minutes. Add vanilla, salt and the rest of the sugar mixture. Beat until it loses its gloss and begins to slightly harden. Drop on waxed paper. Top with a pecan half.

title: custard pie
directions: Chill pie shell while making filling.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of custard comes out clean.
Cool 15 to 30 minutes, then chill in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks over top.
Sprinkle the
dry cake mix over all. Cover with melted butter and top with coconut and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetables eggrolls
directions: Brown garlic in hot oil; add onion.
Saute until transparent. Add ground pork or beef.
Season with soy sauce, pepper, salt and monosodium glutamate (if desired).
Stir until meat is tender. Add first 5 ingredients; keep on stirring until vegetables are tender but firm.
Remove from fire.
Drain remaining broth.
Let cool and set aside.

title: rhubarb sponge pie
directions: Mix together sugar, egg yolks, butter and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
In a nine-inch pie plate, place unbaked pie shell. Spread rhubarb on bottom.
Pour mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until almost done.
Then turn to 375° to brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until well blended.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add egg mixture.
Stir until blended.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 2 bread
pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homestyle tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes.
In separate pan, warm equal proportion milk. Stir soda into tomatoes.
Add tomatoes to milk, stirring constantly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with 1 teaspoon butter when serving.

title: no cook candy
directions: Melt oleo and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Press into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over the top.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: bean casserole
directions: Pour over beans.
Fry 2 onions with 1 1/2 pounds hamburger and 4 sliced bacon, cut up.
Drain.
Mix with bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Toss and mix with dressing.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish in foil. Top fish with all the remaining ingredients.
Seal foil and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Unseal foil and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix flour, sugar and water to make batter.
Pour in melted butter, then add heated peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: sausage stuffed butternut squash(serves 6)
directions: Place squash, cut side down, in greased shallow baking pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until squash is easily pierced.

title: craft . . . holiday candy trains
directions: For each train, glue end of 1 ribbon onto wide side of 1 gum package.
Glue 4 peppermint candies onto side of gum package to make wheels.
Glue roll of ring-shaped candies onto ribbon-topped gum package to make engine.
Glue 1 chocolate kiss and 1 caramel onto engine.
Glue peppermint candies onto sides of 2 rolls of ring-shaped candies and 2 gum packages to make train cars.
Glue remaining ribbon onto top of gum and candy train cars, spacing cars about 1/2-inch apart.
Glue assorted candies onto top of ribbon on gum and candy train cars.
Makes 4 candy trains.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cut leftover roast into bite sizes.
Place on top of stove in a large pan.
Add leftover gravy and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then turn burner to simmer and continue cooking for about 1 hour.
Serve hot!

title: porcupines
directions: Combine all but the soup and shape into balls.
Place in casserole.
Mix the soup with 1 can water and pour over meat. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove lid for the last 15 minutes.

title: cream de menthe cookies
directions: Combine nut meats, vanilla wafer crumbs and powdered sugar. Mix. Add creme de menthe and sugar.
Stir.
Shape into balls.
Roll in grated semi-sweet chocolate.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add green beans, soups, milk and 10 Tater Tots cut in half.
Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Spray dish with vegetable spray if you wish.
Top with remaining Tater Tots and bake at 300° for one hour.
Serves 6. Serve with Italian salad and rolls.

title: hot chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Scrape or break chocolate in top of double boiler, let melt slowly, stirring constantly.
When thoroughly dissolved, pour in water gradually and stir until smooth.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix Carnation, sugar and salt in saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boiling, then cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes, or until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs, oil and nuts with spoon.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
With mixer, mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and chopped nuts.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until top looks like baked meringue.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Cook broccoli until just tender, then mix with cooked rice and remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla carefully.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Cover with topping, then rest of batter.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Marinate steak as directed on package.
In heavy saucepan, saute pepper, onion and mushrooms until tender and lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Brown steak in a little oil.
Remove from pan.
Carefully add marinade seasoning to pan.
Add soup and stir until soup is dissolved.
Add the steak and the vegetables to soup and simmer on medium heat until meat is done.
Can be served over a bed of rice, mashed potatoes or even cooked egg noodles.

title: macaroon cupcakes
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Slowly add 1/2 cup of sugar, beating until stiff, shiny peaks form.
In separate bowl, combine coconut, 1/4 cup sugar, almonds, flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Fold coconut mixture into egg whites. Spoon into 12 paper lined muffin tins.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until a little crusty.
Cool on rack.

title: banana quick bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat until lemon color.
Add banana.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add to mixture.
Add chopped walnuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving. Great with fresh veggies or Hawaiian bread!

title: bibb lettuce salad with oranges and almonds and two dressings
directions: Wash and tear lettuce into salad size pieces.
Place in a bowl and set aside.
Cut onion into rings.
Drain oranges.

title: crab souffle
directions: Dice half of bread and put into baking dish.
Mix crab or shrimp, mayonnaise, onions, green pepper and celery.
Spread over bread.
Place remaining trimmed slices of bread over the top.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over bread.	Refrigerate overnight.	Bake at 325°
for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and spoon soup over top and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 hour longer.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Press through a cookie press onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Drain peaches and slice even thinner.
Melt butter in cake pan in oven.
Add brown sugar; stir to blend.
Put peaches on top. Mix pudding as directed.
Add eggs and cake mix.
Pour this mixture over peaches.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: veal francais
directions: Trim veal and cut into small pieces.
Dip pieces in seasoned flour, then into beaten eggs with parsley.
In butter, brown dipped pieces in a frying pan until they resemble small omelettes.
Remove from pan and place in a roasting pan.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add rhubarb and 1 cup sugar; cook slowly until rhubarb is soft.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks, milk and salt in a bowl.
Add to rhubarb; cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: t's hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough water to make thick.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.

title: layered egg casserole
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered.
Then bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: hummingbird bars
directions: Combine and bake in a greased and floured 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough on 14-inch pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread on top of cookie crust. Add fruits: peaches, pineapple, bananas, cherries, strawberries, kiwi, blueberries. Mix orange marmalade with water and spoon drizzle on top as glaze. Chill.

title: cherry surprise pudding
directions: Combine biscuit mix (Bisquick), milk and brown sugar to make a soft dough.
Spread it roughly in a greased shallow 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chicken italian
directions: Mix
1/2 of the flour with the egg and milk for batter. Dip chicken
in batter, then roll in remaining flour.
Fry in oil until
light
brown.
Drain
on
paper towel then roll in Parmesan cheese
until coated.
Heat sauce, then add chicken. Simmer until bubbly.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: nevelle's buttermilk pound cake(serves 12)
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add soda and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.

title: open-faced mini reubens
directions: Spread 1/2 teaspoon of dressing on each slice of bread.
Place 1 tablespoon of sauerkraut on each slice of bread; top with a slice of corned beef.
Cut cheese the size of bread and place over corned beef.
Arrange sandwiches on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and remove from heat. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add ground beef and toss gently.
Chips can be added just before and while serving.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until done.
Saute onion and pepper until done in small amount of oil.
Mash carrots and stir in onion and pepper.
Make thick cream sauce with butter, flour, pepper and milk.
Mix all together and bake at 350° until bread crumbs are nicely browned.

title: pineapple citrus cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pitcher and chill, covered, for at least 3 hours.

title: margy's hot chez bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on French bread, split in half. Broil until brown and bubbly.
Slice and serve.

title: diabetic lo-cal pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 9-inch pie pan with vegetable spray.
Place all ingredients in blender or mixing bowl. Blend 1 minute or beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into pie pan; bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
Cut in 8 pieces to serve.
One serving equals starch/bread exchange, or 1/2 medium fat exchange.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; save 1/4 cup of juice.
Set aside.
On waxed paper, fix flour and salt.
Use to coat chicken breast halves.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken until golden brown and fork-tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm platter (keep warm).
Into drippings in skillet, stir in honey, teriyaki sauce, chives and pepper.
Heat to boil. Add pineapple; heat through.
Pour over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Top with bread crumbs and brown if desired.

title: great chili soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients and ground beef.
Add other ingredients.
Add water if it is too thick.
Heat 1 1/2 hours.
May be served with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Chill to set.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.
Top with nuts.

title: rice jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium high heat.
Add ground beef; cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add chicken, onion, pepper, celery, garlic and basil leaves.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce; bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir well, then serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed or until tender. Beat soup and cheese together.
Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat the first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes. Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Frost with 2 cups of whipped cream.

title: crock-pot golden glow pork chops
directions: Lightly brown pork chops on both sides in large skillet or slow-cooking pot with browning
unit.
Pour off excess fat. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, cloves,
tomato
sauce, 1/4 cup syrup from peaches and vinegar.
Sprinkle
chops with salt and pepper.
Arrange chops in	slow-cooking
pot.
Place
drained peach halves on top.
Pour tomato mixture over all.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook onions and carrot 3 to 5 minutes in oil.
Add thyme and marjoram and saute 1 minute more.
Add stock, lentils, tomatoes, parsley and salt.
Cook in covered pot 1 1/4 hours.
Add sherry and heat.
Put grated cheese in bottom of bowl and pour hot soup over.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Mix saltines with chicken bouillon, salt and pepper.
In a greased shallow 2-quart casserole, alternately layer cracker mixture and oysters with liquor, making the last layer cracker mix.
Melt butter and add with enough milk to barely cover casserole.
Sprinkle parsley and paprika over top.
Bake at 350° until browned, 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: walnut squares
directions: Combine and bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° about 25 minutes.
Sometimes it takes a little longer.
Cut when still warm.

title: lemon crumb pie
directions: Cover the bread with water, leave for 20 minutes.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten, juice and rind of lemon, butter, salt and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.

title: gelatin ring with cream cheese balls
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in the cranberry sauce until well blended.
Pour into a 6-cup ring mold coated with nonstick cooking spray; refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Roll cream cheese into 3/4 inch balls; coat with walnuts. Unmold gelatin onto a serving platter; place the cream cheese balls in the center of the ring.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cover sweet potatoes with boiling water and cook for 15 minutes.
Drain, peel and cut in half lengthwise.
Arrange in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add fruit and nuts. Add Cool Whip and pour into 9 x 13 glass dish. Freeze.

title: spanikopita(a greek spinach pastry)
directions: Clean, stem and chop spinach.
Salt it lightly and cook, adding no water, for five minutes.
Cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter, salting lightly.
When soft combine with remaining ingredients and spinach (not filo or melted butter).
Spread melted butter on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a strudel leaf (filo) in the pan, it will hang outside the pan.
(Let the edges climb the sides) and brush generously with butter.
Keep layers coming, one on top of another, brushing each with butter.
When you have a pile of 8 leaves, spread on half the filling.
Continue with another stack of 8 or so leaves, then apply the remaining filling, spreading it to the edges.
Fold the excess filo down along the edges, making tidy corners.
Pile as many more layers of filo and butter as your baking pan will accommodate.
Butter top.
Sprinkle with a tablespoon whole anise or fennel seeds if so desired.
Bake uncovered for approximately 45 minutes, until golden at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, chop and drain broccoli.
Place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients except stuffing. Mix and spoon over broccoli.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl; spoon into a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning.
Bake
at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients and oatmeal. Mix thoroughly. Stir in raisins. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and frost with peanut butter frosting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick together.
Roll in small balls, about the size of a walnut.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: diabetic banana cream pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Slice 1 1/2 bananas into the bottom of pie crust.
Pour pudding over the top.
Slice remaining bananas and arrange in circles over the top.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in graham cracker crust.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Place rice in a baking dish lined with aluminum foil.
Add chicken.
Combine soups and pour over rice and chicken.
Sprinkle on onion soup mix.
Seal with foil securely.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ranch style chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in oleo until golden brown. Add soups, tomatoes, green chilies and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole with broken tortilla chips.
Add a layer of chicken, sliced eggs, sauce, cheese and tortillas.
Repeat layers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or microwave for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and eggs.

Stir in milk, cream and oleo. Add pepper, onion and seasonings. Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Set in pan of hot water. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat this solution, then cool.
Mix in gallon jar and keep in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine.
Reserve 1/2 cup stuffing mixture. Spoon remaining stuffing mixture into 2 quart shallow baking dish. Mix sour cream, soup, yellow squash, zucchini, carrots and cheese. Spread over stuffing mixture.
Sprinkle reserved stuffing over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot.

title: perfect chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, margarine, white sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
In a food processor or blender, blend the following ingredients together:
flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix half of dry mixture into moist mixture at a time.
When all the ingredients are added, please add the remaining ingredients:
chocolate chips, Hershey bar (chunked) and chopped nuts.
Place cookie mixture in the refrigerator overnight before baking.
This gives the cookie the perfect look after baking.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add sugar and cream.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Add molasses mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.

title: patty's famous bean soup
directions: In slow cooker, combine water, beans, soup mix and pork hocks. Cook on high for 4 hours.
Add chicken broth, pepper and liquid smoke.
Cook on low for 12 to 14 hours.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut when almost cool.

title: hot pepper jelly(green or red)
directions: Boil peppers, sugar, vinegar and salt 8 to 10 minutes (rolling boil).
Add Certo and boil about 3 more minutes; add coloring. Pour in sterilized jelly jars.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and 3/4 of the cheese in a medium saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until cheese is melted.
Cook each tortilla in hot salad oil for just a few seconds until tortillas are soft.
Drain on paper towels. Spoon 3 tablespoons chicken and 1 tablespoon cheese in each tortilla.
Roll tightly and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Spoon soup mixture over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Garnish with paprika and jalapeno pepper slices.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Place crumbs mixed with melted butter in bottom of shells, reserving half for topping.
Top crumbs with oysters, onion, parsley, spinach and remainder of crumbs.
Dot with butter and fish seasoning.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serve with potato chips and green salad.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and beat until well mixed.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: hawaiian party punch
directions: Combine lemon juice, pineapple juice, sugar and liquor.
Just before serving, pour in the club soda.
Punch may be served in hollowed out watermelon or punch bowl.
Yields 25 punch cup servings.

title: bahamian banana fritters
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder and banana until smooth. Fold in beaten egg. Drop by the spoonful into hot oil. Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and put into a hot casserole containing water and oil.
Cover casserole and bake at 350°
until transparent, about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, parsley and cheese.
Turn off heat and leave in oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix and pour into 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
May be frozen.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put pickles in gallon jar.
Pour vinegar solution over pickles. Leave set in solution 3 or 4 weeks or until you get ready for pickles.
Pour solution off and wash pickles good.
Then put 4 cups sugar over pickles until they make own liquid.
Put in jar and refrigerate.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: crawfish salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, dressing, chili sauce, salt, celery, pickles, shallots and horseradish.
Add eggs and crawfish; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add mixture of flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: delicious lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Combine beans and broth in large pan.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir in lettuce.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Heat and serve.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and saute in 1/2 stick margarine.
Melt the rest of the margarine in boiler on low heat; stir in flour, seasonings and milk.
Add grated cheese to this and let cheese melt. Alternate layers of onions and sauce in 1-quart baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 400°
for 20 minutes.
Very rich, but good.

title: shallot and rosemary glazed steak
directions: Heat a large skillet to hot. Pierce each steak with a fork and place in a shallow bowl. Add 1/3 cup olive oil and 1/3 cup vinegar, rosemary and garlic. Marinate steaks 30 to 45 minutes, turning several times.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Stir butter and cheese, leaving about 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle over top of pie, into the hot macaroni. Add mustard.
Beat eggs into mixture; add milk and mix well.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey (cashew)
directions: Mix.
Place half in bottom of casserole.
Put 1 cup rolled (15) Ritz crackers.
Next, put rest of mix and 1 cup crackers on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler with cake topping
directions: *If canned peaches are used, use 1/2 cup syrup instead of water.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir until creamy; add milk and beat until foamy.
Bake in slow oven, 375°, about 45 minutes.

title: low-fat old fashion banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter and flavoring; cook on low until bubbles.
Add egg.
Add flour to thicken.

title: cheese garlic rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and beat in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in pecans and pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been greased and floured.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until brown.

title: italian sausage
directions: Crush fennel seed until you have 1 tablespoon of powder.
Add 1/2 teaspoon crushed peppers and 4 cloves of garlic, crushed. Thoroughly mix these ingredients with sausage.
Form sausage into balls or chunks to cook in skillet.
Drain grease off sausage.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Brown oleo in pan, then in raw cabbage, salt, pepper and 1 cup water.
Cook until tender.
Add vinegar and sugar to your taste.

title: protestant peanut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from the heat, cool slightly.
In a bowl, cut peanut butter into the confectioners sugar until small crumbs form. (Depending upon the peanut butter you may have to add more confectioners sugar or peanut butter.)
Set aside about 2 tablespoons of crumbs, sprinkle remaining mixture into the pie shell.
(I prefer to reserve some to sprinkle on top of the pudding.)
Pour pudding over crumbs.
Chill until set.
Top with the whipped cream, sprinkle with the 2 tablespoons of crumbs you set aside earlier.
Sometimes I microwave a little peanut butter and a couple drops of water and stir until it is real runny and drizzle over the whipped cream.

title: marjorie's corn pudding
directions: Mix together cornstarch and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, corn and butter.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until firm.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, salt and pepper; drain. Cook macaroni; drain. Add to meat with remainder of ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes and add sour cream, then serve.

title: turtles
directions: Put caramels and water in top of double boiler and cook until melted.
While this is melting, spray a cookie sheet with Pam and arrange pecan halves in clusters on cookie sheet (2 halves if large and if not, 3).
When caramels are melted, drop by teaspoons on pecan clusters, making sure all are covered.

title: creamy strawberry punch
directions: Place strawberries in container of an electric blender. Process until pureed.
Pour into punch bowl; add ginger ale and sherbet.
Stir until creamy.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with fresh strawberries if desired.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Layer cabbage on hamburger meat.
Layer onion, next layer celery.
Add water until water peeps through ingredients. Sprinkle with chili powder.
Simmer until cabbage changes color. Add one can pinto beans (do not drain); add one can tomatoes (run through blender, do not drain); return to stove and simmer as long as you like.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon mint tea
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Pour over tea bags.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Add lemon slices and mint leaves.
Cover and steep 20 minutes.
Strain, discarding tea bags, lemon slices and mint leaves.
Combine tea, remaining 2 cups water, pineapple juice, sugar and flavorings.
Stir well.
Serve beverage over ice and garnish with fresh mint sprigs, if desired.
Yields 6 cups (81 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: chocolate no-bakes
directions: In a saucepan melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa, and milk. Bring to a boil, and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, then peanut butter, stirring until blended.
Stir in oats until you get the thickness you want.
Spoon onto waxed paper (I use an ice cream scoop).

title: chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs; add milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked (Pet-Ritz) pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until set).
Will freeze well.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pennsylvania dutch cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice thin.
Sprinkle with salt.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Rinse and drain.
Pat dry to press out excess liquid.
Combine cucumbers and onion in a large bowl; set aside. In a small bowl, combine other ingredients.
Just before serving, add dressing to cucumbers and toss.

title: cream candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup, milk and salt altogether.
Cook to soft ball stage; add vanilla.
Let cool until lukewarm and beat until thick and creamy.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine 1/4 c. sugar, flour, salt, and baking powder. Cut margarine into dry ingredients until it resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and eggs; stir just to moisten.

title: mike's hard candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in pan and heat to 300° (hard crack stage).
Add oil and stir.
Pour into greased pan; cut and cool.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: An elderly woman was asked her secret for having so many friends.
Her answer contains a lesson every person should learn. She said, "I am always mighty careful to stop and taste my words before I let them pass my lips."

title: cheese spread
directions: Soften and mix with mixer.
Add a dash of sherry vinegar and dash of garlic salt.
Set in refrigerator to thicken and then roll in nuts and serve with crackers.

title: creamy fruit dressing
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, sour cream, honey, poppy seed and finely shredded orange peel.
Stir in enough orange juice to make the dressing of desired consistency.
Spoon over desired cut-up fresh fruit.
Makes 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: "pie pastry"
directions: Mix flour and salt; add shortening.
Mix with fork until particles are the size of a pea.
Add water and stir together. Roll on floured board to desired size.

title: chicken delight(good)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In roaster, mix together the rice, soups and milk.
Lay pieces of uncooked chicken on soup mixture. Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Cook stuffing on top of stove according to directions.
Place on top of chicken.
Cover roaster and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: busy nurses stew
directions: Spray 3 1/2-quart crock-pot with Pam spray or grease with shortening and preheat on high.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot, adding or subtracting vegetables as desired.
Turn crock-pot to low and cook 10 to 12 hours on low or 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: party grits(serves 8)
directions: Bring milk to boil and add 1/2 cup butter in small chunks. Stir until dissolved.
Then stir in 1 cup grits.
Cook, stirring all the time until creamy, like Cream of Wheat.
Remove from stove and beat with electric beater until really creamy.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Allow to set.
Cut into triangular pieces.
Place in casserole in overlapping triangles.
Pour other 1/3 cup butter (melted) and sprinkle cheeses over top.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Coat meat with flour.
Heat oil and butter in a skillet and brown chicken; remove from skillet.
Cook garlic for 30 seconds and remove.
Add mushrooms, onions and soup to skillet.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Return chicken to pan and cook for 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
A great recipe to double or triple for crowds.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients together and simmer 30 minutes.
Brush chicken, beef or pork with sauce while over barbecue.

title: pumpkin pie crunch(serves 16 to 20)
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, spices and salt. Pour into pan. Sprinkle cake mix (dry) evenly over the pumpkin mixture. Top with chopped nuts. Drizzle melted oleo over the top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden top. Cool. Serve with whipped topping. Refrigerate.

title: marinade for barbecue pork
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over pork and marinate for 2 days. Bake in oven on broiler pan at 225° for 3 hours.
I use pork tenderloin.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix by hand the first 3 ingredients. Your batter will have some small lumps. Don't worry, it will be fine. Put in lightly buttered 9 x 13 pan. I use a glass baking dish. Mix dry ingredients with butter and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks, mash and combine with remaining ingredients. Refill egg whites, using pastry tube, if desired.
Chill.
Trim tops with pimiento or paprika.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in boiling water.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish and top with dressing mix.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil until the last 5 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together and pour in skillet.
Bake at 375° until done, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: wilted cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a large skillet.
Remove bacon and drain on paper towels.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Saute pepper in drippings until tender.
Stir in vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage and apples; toss gently. Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Spoon into serving dish.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Serves 6.

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Brown, then drain the ground beef.
Add onion, garlic, salt, tomato sauce and olives.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
In separate bowl, blend cottage cheese, sour cream and chilies.
Crush chips.
Place 1/2 chips in buttered casserole.
Add 1/2 meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Layer until all is gone, but be sure each layer is topped with cheese.
Layer the cottage cheese mixture in, too.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger spanish rice
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add rice and brown 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer slowly until rice is tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough flour to make a thick batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat.
Fry to a golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers and onions; set aside.
Mix together until dissolved (may be heated) the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Mix again.
Put in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 3 or 4 days.
Stir daily.
Can be kept 2 or 3 months in plastic or glass covered dish.
Stir occasionally.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Place in bowl.
Pour buttermilk over chicken. Marinate 1 hour.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken strips in oil and add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and salt.
Simmer until tender (about 1 hour).
Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Add sauce to chicken when tender and mix.
Stir in chunks of pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender, but crisp.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet treat
directions: Slice several small bananas long ways (firm, but ripe bananas).
Arrange on a platter.
(Number depends on amount of people you are serving.)

title: alicia's sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes; peel them, then mash them.
Add 1 cup sugar in them.
Put in butter, cinnamon and flavor.
Cook pie crust for 15 minutes.
Put mixture in pie crust.
Put in oven at 325° until golden brown.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape into patties and brown in frying pan with small amount of oil; drain off excess fat.
Add 1 can of mushroom soup and 1 can of water; pour over meat patties.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix altogether.
Roll out to 1/4 in. thick.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2 in. pie pan.
Bake at 350°F for 15 min. or until desired doneness.
Fill with desired filling.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for beef.
Dice or chop beef and add to mixture (better made a couple of days before needed).

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef in a skillet; drain excess fat.
Add onion and barbecue sauce.
Let simmer while you make the cups.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa and cream together with margarine and eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, coconut and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until well done.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until smooth, about 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or layers.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place all sauces in bottom of crock-pot.
Put in 1 can of beans, 1 layer sausage (cut in bite size pieces), 1/2 chopped onion, green peppers and red pepper.
Continue with another can of beans, sausage, onions and peppers until crock-pot is full.
Cook 1 hour on high and 3 hours on low.
Serve over rice.

title: vera jones' easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt, sugar, shortening and half the flour to yeast.
Beat vigorously until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Place, greased side up, in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator (use within 48 hours).

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix well!
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: raspberry cream souffle
directions: Thaw raspberries and add sugar.
Pour milk, or water into saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin on top and let stand until softened. Melt gelatin over low heat, stirring often.
Stir mixture into raspberries and refrigerate until stiff.
Stir often as it thickens quickly.

title: mushroom crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown mushrooms in butter.
Stir in garlic powder, onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire; cook until liquid evaporates.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; press over bottom and 1/4-inch up sides to form crust.
Spread cream cheese over dough.
Top with mushroom mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes; cut in desired shapes to serve as appetizers.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers. Yields 24 snacks.

title: mock cream of chicken soup(lo-fat)
directions: In a small saucepan, heat stock and bay leaf, uncovered, on medium-high heat until it simmers. Add the chicken and when it re-simmers, reduce the heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes until chicken is no longer pink. Remove from heat.
Remove the chicken and set aside.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Line bottom of casserole with dried beef.
Wrap each split chicken in bacon.
Place on the dried beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup and spread over the chicken breasts.
Top with sauteed mushrooms.
Bake uncovered at 275 degrees for 3 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mashed banana.
Sift in flour with baking powder.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water and add to mixture.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
You may use 2 loaf pans or a Bundt pan.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
The batter will be very thick.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Beat with beater until smooth. Pour over cake mix.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican salad(8 servings)
directions: Shred lettuce.
Chop onions into small pieces.
Rinse chili beans under water and drain.
Combine lettuce, onions, cheese and beans; refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, crush chips.
Add to salad; mix well and top with dressing.

title: tammy's chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 2 minutes. Continue 1 to 2 minutes until smooth. Stir every 30 seconds.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend well with mixer or blender.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with stone ground crackers.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with thawed Cool Whip.
Use mixture and beat until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and spread cherries over entire top.
Return to refrigerator and chill about another hour.
Slice and serve.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sausage and kraut
directions: Cut sausage into desired pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large skillet. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in chopped nuts and all other ingredients, mixing well.
Drop scant teaspoon of mixture onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except baking soda and popped corn in a 2-quart dish.
Cook on Full Power about 2 minutes or until boiling.
Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Put popcorn in brown grocery bag and pour syrup over popcorn.
Close bag and shake.
Cook in bag on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag and cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into pan and allow to cool.

title: fried dough (zalabee)
directions: Mix flour, salt, yeast and oil with water, kneading and leaving mixture soft.
Set until dough rises, about 1 hour.
Cut in strips 2 inches wide by 7 inches longs.
Fry in skillet of hot oil until golden brown.
Upon removing from skillet, sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil; remove from stove and cool. Mix with juices.
When served, mix 2 parts to one part water.

title: lip smackin' punch
directions: Boil 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar; pour in punch bowl.
Add Kool-Aid until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients.
Serve with crushed ice or refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring milk, butter, sugar and cocoa to a boil. Boil 3 minutes. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir. Add oats.
Drop on waxed paper or buttered pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook 2 to 3 hours at 300° in a covered casserole dish.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in small amount hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer (do not boil) until tender, about 1 hour.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Melt gelatine in 1/2 cup boiling water for 10 minutes.
Add soup and heat until hot.
Add cream cheese and stir until smooth. Add shrimp and vegetables.
Cool until slightly thickened and stir to mix again.
Chill overnight or 5 to 6 hours.
Serve with cocktail rye or crackers.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground meat.
Mash tamales with a fork.
Mix browned meat and tamales with other ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together all the ingredients.
Serve with strawberries, pineapple, apples and oranges.

title: apple cream cheese crumb pie
directions: Beat the first four ingredients well and pour over unbaked pie shell.
Combine the next set of ingredients and pour over the cream cheese mixture.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate until chilled. Makes about 1 cup sauce; 100 calories per tablespoon.

title: greek chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken, potatoes and garlic in large roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour broth over.
Whisk olive oil, lemon juice and oregano to combine.
Pour evenly over chicken and potatoes.
Bake until chicken is cooked through and golden brown and potatoes are tender, basting occasionally with pan juices, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over low heat; crush graham crackers.
Add 1 cup peanut butter and box of powdered sugar.
Pour melted margarine over all this; mix well. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Slice before hardens.
Does not need to be refrigerated.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef, soup mix, water and stuffing mix; blend well.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf dish.
Top with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, rotating dish once. Drain off juices.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar and mustard. Spoon over meat loaf.
Microwave, uncovered, for 4 to 5 minutes or until loaf is cooked in center.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: diamond peanut cookies
directions: In a large pan, with a wooden spoon, beat eggs all together, then add sugar, lemon and orange peel and oil. Set aside.
In another bowl, put all the dry ingredients and then add to egg mixture.
Knead into a soft dough, adding more flour if necessary. Roll out into a thin log and flatten with your hand, cut into angles like a diamond shape.
Put on greased tins.
Bake at 350-375° for 18 - 20 minutes to a light golden color.
Cool and frost.
Can also add sprinkles on top.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Make in 3 layers.
For the first layer, melt the margarine and pour over flour and nuts.
Mix and place in long Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hanky-pankies
directions: Fry and drain meat, stir in chunks of cheese until melted. Add other ingredients.
Spread mixture on party rye bread slices and freeze on a flat cookie sheet.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add mayonnaise.
Cook spinach until just separated.
Drain well.
Add cheese to spinach mix and season to taste.
Add spinach to egg mayonnaise.
Stir gently.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in greased dish.
You may substitute chopped broccoli.
Put together in A. M. but do not refrigerate.
Oh, so good, very fattening but worth every calorie.

title: emma joe guiffre's pie crust
directions: Put in cast-iron skillet at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Drop in pie pan and pat down.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add egg.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour before measuring, then sift again with salt and baking powder.
Add milk to butter mixture, then the flour mixture.
Either drop cookies (about 1 teaspoon) or use a cookie press on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 400° or until brown on edges.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain.
Cover with fresh water. Simmer slowly.
Add three beef bouillon cubes.
Cook sufficiently. Drain and add onion, sugar, ketchup, mustard, salt, Worcestershire and 3 bouillon cubes dissolved in boiling water. Place in greased casserole.
Bake, covered, in very slow oven for 6 to 8 hours.
Uncover last hour of cooking.
Add more water, if needed.

title: chicken breasts with new potatoes
directions: Saute chicken breasts in butter on both sides until brown. Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly stir bouillon into hot water. Pour over chicken; cook, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and heat.
Garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 13x9 inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour batter over butter. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to directions and drain.
Combine linguini with the rest of the ingredients.
Toss well and refrigerate overnight.
Parmesan and Romano cheese can also be sprinkled on top.
Recipe doubles and triples easily.
Great for potlucks or large get togethers.

title: emmy's big buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons of warm water.
When yeast is foamy, mix it with 4 tablespoons of the margarine, the potato water (see Note), sugar, salt, milk, eggs and 4 cups flour.
Mix until a ragged dough forms, adding flour as needed.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Grind Triscuits to make crumb topping.
Mix ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Take a large canned ham, remove top of can.
Heat in can in oven long enough to melt the gel.
Pour a bottle of liquid smoke over the ham and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn off oven (do not open door).
Let stand 2 hours.
Slice thinly.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil, zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: baked brie with blue cheese and walnuts
directions: Place Brie in freezer to make slicing easier.
Slice Brie in half horizontally.
Roll out puff pastry, both sheets.
Beat egg and brush egg on inside of puff pastry.
Place Blue cheese on top of cut side of bottom half of Brie.
Place chopped walnuts over the Blue cheese.
Replace top half of Brie.
Place between pastry sheets.
Brush edges with melted butter and make seam.
Seal on bottom.
Brush entire top and sides with melted butter.
Place in baking pan with sides (not flat cookie sheet).
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.
Let set 45 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
If cut too early it will be runny.
This is a great party pleaser!

title: doug's apple dip
directions: Presoften cream cheese.
Cream all ingredients together and serve with apple slices.
Alternating slices of red and yellow centered with dip makes a really attractive and delicious party platter.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and put into a large baking dish. Top with the corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease a large pizza pan or sheet cake pan.
Pat out rolls onto pan.
Sprinkle with potatoes and sausage.
Add salt and pepper to eggs.
Pour eggs over potatoes and sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, 2 sugars, and oil. Beat in eggs and add vanilla. Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda, and salt. Stir in creamed mixture. Place all in a plastic bowl and store in the refrigerator over night covered. Pinch off pieces and shape into small balls. Roll balls into granulated sugar. Place on cookie sheet and flatten each ball with a glass. Bake at 325 for 8 - 10 minutes. Cool 2 -3 minutes with pan on wire rack.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into cakes and place into greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mahogany pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Gradually add sugars, beating about 6 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, cocoa and soda.
Add to butter mixture with sour cream alternately.
Beat at low speed until blended; stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an airtight container.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Marinate meat at least 4 hours. (Best if marinated overnight.)
Cook in dehydrator.

title: swiss steak supreme
directions: With edge of saucer, pound steak well on both sides to tenderize.
Cut into serving pieces.
Dredge with flour.
Brown well in enough hot oil to cover bottom of skillet.
Season to taste with onion and garlic salts and pepper.
Mix together soups, carrots with liquid, and tomato sauce.
Pour over steak.
Cook, tightly covered, over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Turn meat and stir sauce twice during cooking.

title: western style baked beans
directions: Brown 1 c. of ground chuck.
Cut the smoked sausage into 1/2 inch sections.
Mix the ground chuck, sausage and all other ingredients in a large casserole dish or stoneware Dutch oven. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Secret family recipe.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Old English cheese.
Then crumble in Blue cheese.
Only use a small portion at a time, not to make it too strong. Use nuts or cracker crumbs for topping after you roll into a ball.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Beat whipping cream until it forms soft peaks.
Add chocolate syrup until blended.
Layer crackers on a tray.
Frost with the cream.
Continue to layer crackers and frosting with cream. Leave a little bit of cream to frost the top and sides.
Sprinkle jimmies on top of cake (optional).

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: *Make this mixture up twice.

title: punch(serves 100)
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Heat to a hard boil.
While still hot, add jello.
Color and flavor for occasion with lemon, orange and pineapple juices.
Stir until all ingredients are dissolved.
Add water and almond extract.
Divide into 3 equal parts and freeze. Add a 2 liter ginger ale to each part punch mixture.

title: white sauce
directions: Place margarine in a 1-quart glass bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper making a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk, blending well.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium for 6 to 9 minutes or until sauce is thickened and bubbly, stirring occasionally. Makes 2 cups.

title: quick apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, dump dry cake mix and all other ingredients. Beat on high about 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix together 1/2 cup mayonnaise, celery soup and lemon juice.
In large casserole dish, layer broccoli, chicken, cheese and sauce. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake until brown at 350° or 375°.

title: ham-stuffed bell peppers
directions: In a large skillet, melt the 1/4 cup butter.
Add the onion, celery and garlic; cook until tender.
Add the ham, undrained tomatoes and tomato juice.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until liquid is slightly reduced.
Stir in 1 cup of the crushed crackers, the egg, sugar, hot pepper sauce and ground red pepper.
Meanwhile in a large saucepan, cook the green pepper halves in boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes; invert to drain.
Fill pepper halves with the ham-vegetable mixture.
Arrange peppers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: buist's fudge pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Blend in vanilla and dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pie pan (8-inch). Bake in preheated oven at 325° until pie is set.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounce white almond bark in 2 quart bowl on High 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes until smooth, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries. Sprinkle with coconut.
Microwave remaining almond bark until smooth, drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Store at room temperature.
Makes about 12 wedges.

title: corny broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla ice cream to each cup.
Serves 35 to 40.

title: mom's potato leek soup
directions: Cook leeks, ham and garlic in butter in large pot over medium heat until leeks are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add broth, cabbage, potatoes and bay leaf, simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in cream; continue to simmer until heated through.
Garnish with parsley and chives.

title: yummy cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflowerets in 1-inch of boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Saute, in margarine, celery, green pepper and onion.
Blend in salt, pepper and flour.
Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.

title: golden sun breakfast drink
directions: Combine pineapple juice, egg, honey and wheat germ in blender. Peel and slice banana into mixture. Whirl smooth.

title: icebox lemon-lime pie
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and food coloring.
Pour into graham crust.
Put into refrigerator until set, about 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased loaf pan.

title: easy potato cheese soup
directions: Melt oleo in medium pan, add flour to oleo.
Add water, bouillon cubes and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat 10 minutes.
