Stir in potato soup and soup can of milk.
Lower heat and cook 10 more minutes.
Right before serving, add 3/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Serves 4.

title: bellingham blueberry scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together in large bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in yogurt and egg whites just until dough leaves side of bowl.
Add blueberries. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, knead lightly 10 times. Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Pat into 8 inch circle, using floured hands.
Cut circle into 12 wedges with sharp knife dipped in flour, do not separate wedges.
Brush with milk or yogurt.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 18-20 minutes or until edges brown and toothpick comes out clean.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Wash and slice eggplants 1/2-inch thick.
Salt; let drain on paper towel.
Saute until slightly brown in olive oil.
Layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Beat 4 eggs and pour over above mixture.
Pour over 2 cups of stewed tomatoes.
Layer more cheese on top (Mozzarella and Parmesan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers, onions and peppers. Let set half a day.

title: cook in oven chocolate pie
directions: Mix in blender.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Gradually add cream to cream cheese, blending until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: ozark mt. apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to shortening mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples by hand.
Bake in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Bake for 6 minutes at 450°.

title: cherry pineapple pie
directions: Set aside egg whites for meringue.
Mix remaining ingredients (except pie crust) together and cook over low heat until thickens.
Pour into baked crust.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Spread on pie and brown slightly.

title: green fettuccine soup
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain and toss with 1 tablespoon of the oil.
In a large saucepan heat remaining oil; saute onion, then garlic.
Add the stock and bring to a boil.
Add the spinach, ham, nutmeg and pepper.
Simmer 4 minutes and then add noodles and heat through, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Ladle soup into bowls and serve with the Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: bologna sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more dressing, if you need, for right consistency to spread.

title: autumn pork chop dinner
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil on high.
Brown chops on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
Toss cabbage with parsley and brown sugar.
Place in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with potatoes and beans.
Arrange chops over.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Pour apple juice over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the pork chops and vegetables are tender.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, cracker crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Form small meatballs.
Brown in oil.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; set aside.
Remove meatballs from pan; drain off fat. Put soy sauce, vinegar, water and pineapple in pan.
Add sugar and cornstarch; stir until thickened.
Add green peppers and pineapple.
Return meatballs to pan.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: fantastic fish(weight watchers logo)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute onion and garlic in half of margarine until onion is clear.
Add parsley, oregano, bread crumbs, crabmeat and water to form a stuffing. In medium size casserole layer 3/4 pound fish, stuffing mixture and remaining fish.
Top with remaining 2 tablespoons diet margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.

title: maple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Drop by little teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Combine buttermilk and baking soda.
Add sifted ingredients to first mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add persimmon pulp and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 75 minutes.
Cool and frost with Buttermilk Frosting (recipe follows).

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut peaches in pie filling into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: grape-juice lemonade
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given.
Chill for half an hour.
Serve in each glass a thin slice of lemon from which the seeds have been removed.

title: sausage balls
directions: Note: Sausage and cheese should be room temperature to mix well.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; set aside.
In skillet, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter buckeyes
directions: Blend peanut butter, margarine and sugar with a wooden spoon. Knead with hands until mixture is smooth. Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Shave paraffin.
Place half of the paraffin with half of the chocolate morsels in a saucepan.
Heat over low fire until chocolate melts.
Pour into cup.
Spear balls with a toothpick and dip each ball into chocolate until it is almost covered.
Remove toothpick.
Place the buckeye down so that the peanut butter opening is on top.
Repeat with remaining peanut butter balls. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: virginia's squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Mix soup, sour cream (yogurt) and carrots.
Add squash and onion. Set aside.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix. Spread half of the stuffing mix in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Spread with vegetable mixture and top with rest of stuffing mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in large bowl.
Put 1/2 of the Cool Whip in with cottage cheese then put jello in.
Drain mandarin oranges and put oranges in cottage cheese mixture.
Now you then put remainder of Cool Whip in and mix thoroughly with spoon.
Refrigerate for about one hour then serve.
Serves 5 people.
(Approximate cost: $7.00.)

title: french-style green bean casserole
directions: Drain juice from corn and beans and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together sour cream and cream of celery soup; pour over corn and beans.
Put chopped onion and grated cheese over the soup.
Melt margarine.
Mix the margarine with Stove Top stuffing.
Put this on top.
Heat until bubbly.

title: walterspiel(potato, leek soup)
directions: Saute bacon in a deep saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add leeks and onion and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth slowly, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and simmer for 1 hour. Combine egg yolks and sour cream and stir them into soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add parsley and chervil. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: elvis presley's favorite cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate flour and cream.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put into casserole. Crumble 1 stack crackers (saltine or Ritz) put over top.
Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: cheesed broccoli for two
directions: Unwrap broccoli.
Place in a shallow microproof dish.
Cover with plastic wrap. Cook on High for 8 minutes. Drain.
Sprinkle cheese over broccoli.
Cook, uncovered, on High 45 seconds.

title: fruit bars
directions: Put all together in blender and mix.
Pour into 5-ounce paper cups.
Place a stick in each cup and freeze.

title: cheese mix(microwave)
directions: In small bowl, add salt and Worcestershire sauce to margarine; mix well.
Pour Chex, nuts and pretzels into a gallon sized Ziploc bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture in bag.
Seal and shake.
Pour into large bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: bayou beef-rice dish
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add flour.
Cook until lightly brown, stirring constantly.
Add onions.
Saute until transparent.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Cook stirring constantly, until ground beef is lightly brown.
Add 2 cups water.
Simmer for 2 hours, adding additional water as needed to prevent sticking. Add rice, parsley and shallots.
Heat thoroughly.

title: spinach or broccoli soup
directions: In saucepan, combine vegetables and broth.
Bring to a boil, uncovered, and simmer 5 minutes or until the vegetables are limp. Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Stir in flour and pepper; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Gradually blend in milk, then sour cream. Stir in vegetable mixture.
Heat through; serve in cups.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: eggs newport
directions: Slice hard-cooked eggs in baking dish.
Blend soup with mayonnaise.
Gradually add milk, stirring until well blended.
Add chopped onion.
Pour over eggs.
Sprinkle crispy cooked bacon crumbled around edge of dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Combine meat and onion with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup of water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimento, salt and dash of pepper; mix well.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and oleo; sprinkle on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until hot.
Trim with green pepper rings.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: date nut roll
directions: Save out 1/4 of the crushed cracker and roll nuts and dates in.
Pour milk over marshmallows and let stand.
Then stir until the marshmallows melt some. Mix all ingredients together and pour in a loaf pan (or whatever you want to use).
Let set overnight and take out of pan.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
It will keep in the refrigerator for a long time.

title: oatmeal date cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix. Blend in vanilla. Sift together flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt and add to creamy mixture. Add slowly and mix. Then add all dry ingredients to your mixture. Drop spoon size cookie mixture onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: herb roasted onions
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch foil pan, combine sugar, vinegar and 1/4 c. of the broth.
Place onions, cut side down, in pan.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Set pan on cooking grate.
Place lid on grill.
Cook until most of the liquid has evaporated (40 to 45 minutes).

Add remaining broth and gently stir to loosen browned drippings. Continue to cook until onions are tender (10 to 15 more minutes). Let stand for about 10 minutes after removing from grill to serving dish.
Turn cut side up to serve.
Serve warm.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cukes, onions and red and green peppers with cold water. Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Simmer until tender.
Can in jars.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice; set this aside.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and Mandarin oranges and fold in Cool Whip. Garnish with crushed graham crackers and chill several hours or overnight.

title: hawaiian spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and serve as dip with Hawaiian bread or chips.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth; 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken salad
directions: Cut and clean broccoli.
Blanch for 5 minutes with 2 tablespoons of oil in water.
Drain and chill.
Poach chicken breasts, also drain and chill.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine 1 large (8 servings) package strawberry jello and 2 cups sugar.
Add 2 cups boiling water to dissolve jello and sugar. Add 1 1/2 cups cold water and chopped fruits.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: out-of-this-world cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat and add cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Add baking powder.
Mix and then add milk.
Divide batter into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cakes test done. Remove from pans and assemble cake with icing.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni and drain.
In a saucepan, melt the butter and remove from heat.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in the milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then reduce heat.
Simmer about 1 minute and remove from heat.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar, flour, salt, lemon juice and spices.
Add beaten egg and mix thoroughly.
Add milk gradually and stir smooth.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Make your favorite crust or buy frozen one or Pillsbury ready to use.
Add 1 can Lucky Leaf apple pie filling.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until set and browned at 325° to 350°.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Pour soup and sour cream (mixed together) over potatoes.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with crumbled corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: harvest fruit mold
directions: Combine fruit and enough water to cover in a saucepan. Simmer gently, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes, adding sugar for the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in syrup mixture.
Chill until partially set.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 300°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples, core and half.
Roll out biscuits and wrap around apple halves.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° until brown, basting every 15 minutes.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix meal, flour, sugar, egg and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add shortening.
Pour in Pam sprayed loaf pan to within 1 inch of top. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients into soft dough, sifting baking powder into flour.
Roll dough as thin as pie crust.
Bake in a quick oven (450°) until light brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and Hawaiian Punch.
Add sherbet.
Pour Sprite or 7-Up over sherbet when ready to serve.

title: apple custard
directions: In mixer, beat egg, cinnamon, vanilla and melted butter.
Stir apples with sugar.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.
Very delicious and freezes well.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Mix pudding and condensed milk (blend well).
Chill for 10 minutes.
Take out and fold in Cool Whip.
Let chill again for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken into bite-sized pieces and put into casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Mix broth from chicken with stuffing mix until sticky.
Spread on top of soup-sour cream mixture.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix until thin.
Add pecans.
Pour into shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad(easy and delicious)
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding well in bowl.
Then add other ingredients, mix well and chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken chip bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
After you mix your ingredients, put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle mixture with cheese and chips.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Partially cook bacon; add onion.
Cook until onion reaches clear stage.
Remove bacon and onion and place in crock-pot or such.
Cook beef in remaining bacon fat.
Add beef and remaining ingredients to crock-pot and stir together.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients with hand mixer or in blender.
Use for dipping raw vegetables, chips, pretzels, etc.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until of spreading consistency.

title: homemade ketchup
directions: Wash, peel and cut up tomatoes.
Cook, strain and boil again to boiling, until 3/4 previous amount.
Stir frequently.
Add vinegar, paprika, sugar and salt.
Add ketchup, spice and onions.
Cook until thick.
Pour in pint jars.
Let seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: stuffed peppers with rice and bacon
directions: Cut tops from peppers and clean insides.
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Cook rice with curry powder; drain and cool.
Mix rice, bacon and drippings, onion, celery, cheese, parsley and mushrooms together.
Stuff peppers with mixture and bake with 1 can of tomatoes to cover at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water all together until thick. Add nuts and cool. Set aside.
Mix the shortening, brown sugar, vanilla, eggs, soda, baking powder, salt and flour.

Mix well and roll out to about 1/2-inch thick. Spread on filling and roll up like a jelly roll. Chill for at least 4 hours. Freezing is also okay. Slice and bake on a floured cookie sheet for about 8 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Soften margarine and work into powdered sugar.
Use enough milk to form a stiff dough.
Roll out on surface dusted with powdered sugar.
Spread peanut butter on top of dough.
Roll up and freeze, then cut into slices crosswise.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, melted butter, vanilla, syrup, salt and cocoa.
Mix well.
Arrange pecans in pie crust.
Pour filling over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then lower oven temperature to 300° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into florets and blanch until tender but still crunchy; cool.
Combine broccoli, sunflower seeds, bacon, onion, and raisins.
In a small bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar together to make dressing.
Pour over the broccoli mixture and toss. Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes lots of cookies.

title: "strawberry stuff"
directions: Using mixer, beat milk into pudding.
Mix together with cake cubes and press into 8 x 13 x 2 pan or casserole.
Mix strawberries with strawberry glaze.
Spread this over the cake cubes with pudding.
Let stand a couple hours or overnight.
Cover with "lite" Cool Whip.
Can be garnished on top with a few pieces of strawberries or even blueberries.
Enjoy!!

title: poor man's cake(eggless, milkless, butterless cake)
directions: Boil together the sugar, water, shortening, salt, raisins and spices for 5 minutes.
When cold, add flour and soda dissolved in a teaspoon of hot water.
This makes 2 loaves.
Bake approximately 45 minutes in 325° oven.
This cake is of good texture and keeps moist for sometime.

title: johnny masatta
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soups and sour cream.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peach ambrosia
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut and spoon into sherbet glasses.

title: suet pudding
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add molasses and milk to suet. Combine mixtures.
Turn into buttered mold and cover.
Steam 3 hours.
Raisins and currants may be added.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in crock-pot.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; pour over meat.
Stir to coat meat with flour.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 4 to 5 hours.
Stir thoroughly before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, rice, soup, water, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Serves 6.

title: treasure bars
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Cut in butter. Press in greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: low calorie vegetable soup(meatless)
directions: In 2 quarts of water, add cut up vegetables.
Do not use any starchy vegetables.
If desired, use 1 envelope onion soup mix, bouillon or low-fat broth.
Season to taste with Mrs. Dash seasoning or your own preference.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
One cup equals 25 calories.
If on low-sodium diet, use low-sodium soup base or low-sodium spices.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Stir in sweet potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Beat.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scotch tea tarts
directions: Mix above ingredients and chill 1/2 hour.
Spread mixture evenly over bottom of jelly roll pan, which should be lined with foil.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. pecans.
Mix eggs with brown sugar, butter, salt, and vanilla.
Spread over dough.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Can be frozen.

title: healthy carrot-raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine the baking soda and warm water, and set the mixture aside.
In a large bowl, combine the carrots, yogurt, sugar, applesauce, oil, whole egg or egg whites, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt (if desired) and raisins.
Stir in the whole wheat flour and all-purpose flour, then stir in the reserved baking soda mixture.
Pour the batter into a greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Place the pan in the hot oven, and bake the cake for 1 hour or until a tester inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
Let the cake cool in the pan on a rack for about 10 minutes before turning the cake out onto the rack to cool completely.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and garlic until onion wilts. Add chicken. Cook until brown.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer about 6 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: snappy sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix in a blender until consistency is smooth.
Serve with potato or nacho chips.

title: spicy pork chops
directions: Dice onions, green peppers and carrots.
Place pork chops in a large skillet with 1 cup of water and cook until tender.
When pork chops are tender, add all the diced vegetables plus 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Simmer until vegetables are tender (if the mixture becomes dry before done, add water and simmer).

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes with sour cream, soup, onion, melted margarine and cheese in a bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: veggie chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium-high heat, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add chicken broth, carrots, potatoes, green beans, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg together.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add choice of chips and/or nuts.
Bake at 350° or 375°, depending on oven.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, placing about 2-inches apart.
Bake for about 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine flour, potatoes, salt, beaten egg yolks and liquid. Fold in egg whites and bake on greased griddle.

title: butterscotch bananas
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together brown sugar and rum. Add
butter;
cover.
Microwave
at
High
to
5 minutes, or until sugar is dissolved.
Cut bananas lengthwise, then crosswise, so there are 8 pieces.
Add to syrup, carefully coating each
piece.
Microwave
at
High 1 to 2 minutes or until hot. Serve over ice cream.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Dilute soup with 1 can of water; mix well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unroll and separate rolls.
On each roll, put chicken, jalapeno cheese and onion.
Roll up each roll; place in soup mixture and turn to coat.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Spoon into crust. Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping, chocolate shavings or fruit if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding the pecans last.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour drained pineapple in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
(Save 10 tablespoons juice).
Mix sugar, flour and juice.
Pour over pineapple.
Put 1 cup shredded cheese on top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.
Top with Ritz and butter.
Return to oven to brown topping.

title: kerri's soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: rainbow trout
directions: Take whole trout and put 1/2 lemon into cavity.
Salt and pepper cavity.
Put 2 pats butter into it also and wrap in aluminum foil to form a boat.
Wrap it all the way around trout. Cook on open fire with hot coals for 5 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in two round cake pans.
Set aside to cool.
Prepare instant pudding as directed. Set in refrigerator to cool.

title: french new potato salad
directions: Sauce:
Combine all the ingredients in a food processor.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook grits in water with salt for 5 to 6 minutes.
Brown sausage in a skillet, then drain.
In a large bowl, combine grits, sausage and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except for the last 3; place in Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with the grated cheese, crushed corn flakes or potato chips and toasted almonds.
Cover with Saran Wrap; refrigerate until ready for baking.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a pot and boil for one minute.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
While chops are browning, heat soup, water and rice in microwave.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Place pork chops in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour rice mixture over the top of chops.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: Combine punch mix, juice, sugar and orange drink powder in a 6-quart punch bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add water and stir.
Slowly add Diet 7-Up, just before serving, and stir.
If desired, add orange slices for garnish.
Yields 30 (6-ounce) servings.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting (see below) when cool.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and flour.
Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn. Mix well.
Stir in peppers, onions and cheese.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: poor man's cake(no eggs)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add 2/3 cup shortening, then add hot water and raisins.
Mix until all is blended while hot so shortening melts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple and poppy seed loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, combine 1/4 cup of the reserved pineapple juice, pineapple, orange juice, zest, milk, eggs, sugar, oil and poppy seed. Combine the dry ingredients; add the pineapple mixture, folding the batter just enough to moisten all the ingredients. Do not overmix. Pour into greased pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out to cool completely on a wire rack before slicing.

title: spiced pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a small saucepan, melt 2/3 cup of butter. Stir in brown sugar. Spread in the bottom of an ungreased heavy 12-inch skillet or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Arrange pineapple in a single layer over sugar mixture. Place a cherry in the center of each slice. Sprinkle with pecans and set aside.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Sit in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together, then fold in 9 ounce container of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sweet potatoes and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until moistened. Drain raisins; stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Grease two 12-cup muffin pans.
Sprinkle mixture of 2 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon over greased surface.
Shake to spread evenly, discarding excess.
Beat together eggs, remaining sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared pans.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cold.

title: banana bread with chocolate chips
directions: Mix bananas in bowl.
Then add wet ingredients and mix.
Now mix dry ingredients and add 1/2 to 1 whole bag of chocolate chips. Pan size:
Loaf pan Yield 2 loaves.

title: simmering pork chops
directions: Grease Dutch oven.
Flour pork chops lightly.
Brown both sides on stove, then add all ingredients except potatoes and carrots.
Cook pork chops in oven for 1 hour at 375°.
Add a little more water and salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cook 1 more hour.
Serve piping hot.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: In large skillet, sear steak on both sides over high heat. Reduce heat to low; add onion soup and cream of mushroom soup. Add 1 soup can water.
Peel potatoes and cut into fourths and add to skillet.
Cover and cook 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery; add potatoes.
In a separate saucepan, combine butter, flour and milk; heat and stir until mixture becomes a thick sauce.
Add to potato mixture.
Add additional milk to desired thickness.
Add fried and crumbled bacon to soup.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together on high.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch non greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean. Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: peanut butter butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
In medium saucepan, melt butterscotch and peanut butter bits and margarine. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 the mixture firmly in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in the condensed milk, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Pour onto crust; top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake for 25 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool at room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: duffie's deer camp chili
directions: This recipe will feed 15 hungry deer hunters.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and stir in milk.
Add other ingredients.
Stir over low to medium heat until smooth.
Serve over cooked vegetables.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips about 2 1/2 x 1-inches.
Pound strips to help make tender.
Brush soy sauce on each side of meat, then sprinkle with flour.
Brown steak strips in oil over medium heat. Add green pepper and saute a few minutes.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes until meat is tender.

title: peanut butter crisps(student favorite)
directions: Mix cereal and peanuts; set aside.
Combine sugar and syrup. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour hot syrup mixture over cereal mixture, stirring to coat the cereal.
Pat cereal evenly into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cool and cut into 2-inch bars.
Makes 16.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Cook penne until just al dente.
Drain in a colander and rinse with cold water.
Drain again until very dry.
Place in a bowl and toss with olive oil.
Mix in Mozzarella, vinegar, Parmesan, tomatoes and basil.
Add salt and pepper.
Makes 8 side-dish servings.

title: warm tortellini and tomato
directions: Prepare tortellini according to directions on package.
Keep tortellini warm.
Heat about 1/8 cup olive oil with garlic.
Remove from heat and pour over tortellini in a large serving dish.
Add tomato, warmed oil, pepper to taste and sprinkle with a couple of tablespoons of each cheese.
Serve warm.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients.
Good microwaved on saltine cracker, in a sandwich or as a dip.

title: christmas fruitcake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs. Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and fruit.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Put frozen hash browns in 13 x 9 pan and coat with melted margarine. Combine sour cream, onions, cheese, soup, salt and pepper. Add to potatoes in pan, but don't mix. Combine corn flakes and margarine; sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly.
(I sometimes leave overnight, adding enough ice to last.) Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to boiling. Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a medium sized bowl, mix the powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth; divide into 2 prepared graham cracker or butter crusts.
Top with cool strawberry glaze.
Place 1 tablespoon Cool Whip in the middle.
Arrange fresh strawberries around crown of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on Cool Whip.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Melt over low heat; set aside.

title: red cloud kooler
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and water according to package directions; add frozen strawberries, dry ice and ice cream.
More of each may be added as needed.
Yields 25 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to gelatin.
Drain juice from pineapple and add cold water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Chill.
Grind cranberries and orange and add sugar. When gelatin begins to thicken, add fruit mixture.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn off cobs into medium bowl.
Combine corn, butter, cream, sugar and pepper in a skillet.
Cover. Let simmer for 6 to 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: perfect blender popovers
directions: Put eggs and milk in blender; blend until bubbly.
Add flour and salt.
Blend until smooth.
Fill well-greased muffin cups half full.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and save 1/4 cup of liquid.
Arrange asparagus in a square dish, which has been buttered.
Cover asparagus with chopped eggs.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Mix 1/4 cup of asparagus liquid and mushroom soup.
Pour over asparagus and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
and pour into buttered casserole, 8
x 10-inches.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Great with ham or chops.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1 cup pumpkin.
Add whipped topping (Dream Whip).
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped topping.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce and soda water.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add them with floured raisins to the first mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hunters stew
directions: In greased casserole, put layers as given.
Pour can of tomato soup over top.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake for 1/2 hour more.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add large can pork and beans. Mix into beef.
Add several tablespoons each of catsup, mustard, Heinz 57 and about 1/4 to 1/2 cup brown sugar.
I never measure.
I just dump them in.
Ready to serve in about 10 to 15 minutes, or could be baked for an hour or so to dry them out.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite size pieces including stems. Combine with onion, raisins and bacon, crumbled.
Mix with dressing.

title: blueberry grunt(nova scotia classic)
directions: Pour blueberries into a skillet (include water from cans). Stir in sugar and cook until the first sign of bubbles.
Mix dry ingredients and orange rind.
Stir in milk.
This makes 8 dumplings.
Drop dumplings by spoonfuls on top of simmering blueberries.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes or until dumplings are doubled in size.
(Cover lid tightly, then listen to the dumplings grunt! Is that where the name came from?)
Serve dumplings with sauce and top with thick cream.

title: choc-date bars
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips. Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar and milk. Put in 9 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Whip egg.
Very slowly add small portion of oil until egg and oil are well blended.
Continue whipping and slowly adding the oil until all the oil is gone.
The mixture should be somewhat like a mayonnaise consistency.
When stirring, go in the same direction. Only if the egg and oil separate, you must then start over.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic powder to taste (generally 10 good shakes of garlic powder is sufficient).
If you choose to use garlic salt, do not add any regular salt.
(Note:
Garlic powder is 5 times as strong as garlic salt.)
Or you can choose to use fresh ground garlic.
Add lemon juice.
If using a fresh lemon, squeeze one half of the lemon.
Add the Parmesan cheese and anchovies or anchovy paste if you like.
Taste with a small piece of lettuce. If something doesn't taste quite right, add more garlic powder.

title: bean dip
directions: Begin with first ingredient.
Spread beans on a platter and continue layering in order of ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add coconut mix.
Add flour and soda to mixture.
Form into balls.
Press with fork dipped in sugar. Makes 8 dozen cookies.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: collard greens
directions: Heat 1/2 c. broth in large dutch oven over medium heat until hot. Add garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Add greens and remaining broth; stir well. Cover and cook 7-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir in red pepper and salt.

title: fruit cake
directions: Spray tube pan with Pam and line with wax paper.
Then spray and flour again.
Sift flour and soda.
Mix eggs and mincemeat, condensed milk, fruit and nuts.
Stir in flour and pour in pan. Bake at 300° for about 2 hours or until center springs back when lightly touched and is golden brown.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate.
Heat vinegar and butter until hot in microwave.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Add to vinegar and butter.
Cook until thick.
When cool, add sour cream.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Toss until all is coated.
Chill, then serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soup and 1/2 of the onions.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and add rest of onions and Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven and melt cheese.

title: microwave lemon bars
directions: Combine butter, 1 cup flour and powdered sugar and cut into fine crumbs with a fork.
Press in bottom of 9-inch square pan. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until surface looks dull.
Mix eggs, lemon juice, rind, baking powder, sugar and flour.
Mix and pour over baked crust.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on 70% power for 5 to 7 minutes or until set, about 1 inch from the center.
Cool, covered, on countertop.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: tomato jelly
directions: Boil mixture for 15 minutes.
Pour into jelly glasses.
Let cool completely.
Pour paraffin wax on top to seal.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Add salt, oil and sugar to milk and heat to 120° to 130°. Pour mixture over yeast.
Add flour and mix well.
Scrape dough onto a heavily floured surface (dough will be sticky).
Liberally sprinkle top of dough with more flour.
Roll out, cut into rounds with biscuit cutter and brush with butter.
Fold over and allow to rise on cookie sheet for 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: fish stick casserole
directions: Prepare mixed vegetables according to package; drain.
Add the clam chowder and milk.
Pour mixture into shallow casserole. Cover; bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Uncover; put fish sticks on top.
Bake for about 12 minutes, or until fish sticks are brown and crisp.

title: cold oven pound cake(club member: terah smith)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Separate eggs; beat egg whites and set aside. Add egg yolks to butter and sugar. Add flour and milk. Fold in egg whites; add flavoring. Put in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bean and squash casserole
directions: Layer an 11 x 7 x 1/2-inch baking dish with 1 can of mushroom soup.
Pour beans, slightly drained, over soup.
Layer with sliced squash; break up bacon over squash.
Layer with thin slices of onion and top with can of mushroom soup.
Cover with Saran Wrap (leaving one corner open for steam) and cook in microwave 25 minutes or in regular oven at 350° for 1 hour.
(Don't cover in regular oven.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour with sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir butter to soften.
Add flour mixture, buttermilk, vanilla, eggs and chocolate.
Blend.
Then beat 3 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pans 15 minutes, then remove from pans. Finish cooling on rack.
Spread frosting between layers and over top.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, lemon juice and water in saucepan.
Cook until sauce is clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; chill.
Line pie shell with 3 ounces cream cheese, softened with milk.
Mix sauce with peaches.
Spread over cream cheese. Whip the cream; add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon lemon juice. Spread over peaches.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with peach slices.

title: blueberry breakfast bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in blueberries (batter will be thick).
Spread into greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fast and easy fruit crispsocorro, new mexico
directions: To bake:
Spread pie filling in low rasting pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit filling.
Drizzle with melted butter, sprinkle with nuts.

title: little ham roll-ups
directions: Mix with mayonnaise to spreading consistency.
Spread on ham. Roll up by short end.
Chill rolls overnight.
Slice.
Serve on toothpick or cracker.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, using 2 round layers. Mix Cool Whip, 2 packages coconut and sour cream and sugar. Split cake layers to make 4 layers; stack with split side up. Spread icing between each layer, sides and top, then top with remaining coconut.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thaw frozen pie shell 20 minutes.
Crimp edge to stand 1/2-inch above rim.
Preheat oven with cookie sheet at 375°.
Bake pie on cookie sheet 70 minutes or until tests done.
Turn pie at 35 minutes to assure even baking.
Knife inserted near center of pie tests clean.
Recipe is combination of Libby's Joy of Cooking and my own variations.

title: pineapple cheese cake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 2 cups flour, 2/3 cup margarine, 1/2 cup finely chopped toasted almonds and 1/2 cup powdered sugar until crumbly.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together the vanilla wafers, chopped nuts and butter and bake at 350° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: garden bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Place in a large bowl; add green pepper, celery, pimientos and green onions.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugar to eggs 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice to egg mixture.
Fold flour mixture into egg mixture until blended.
Spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up and cool.
Unroll cake, spread on filling.
Reroll cake.
Place roll, seam-side down. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: In glass pie dish, smooth softened cream cheese.
Spread canned chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or put in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together several times.
Beat the eggs and oil.
Add this mixture, the crushed pineapple and juice and the bananas together.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt Nestle's butterscotch morsels with peanut butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until blended. Stir in Rice Krispies. Press half of mixture into buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill. Set remainder aside.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles in advance, as well as having chicken cooked and deboned into bite size pieces.
In large bowl, mix all remaining ingredients.
Stir in chicken and noodles.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole.
(This will probably fill 2 pans.)
Bake 1 hour, covered.

title: creamed chicken casserole
directions: Roll chicken breast in flour to coat.
Brown in skillet in 1 tablespoon butter; put aside.
In small casserole dish, blend sour cream and soup.
Add chicken in and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour over rice when baked.

title: capellini amanda(a light and easy dish served over angel hair pasta)
directions: In olive oil, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Add cans of tomatoes.
Simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Add red wine vinegar, salt, pepper, basil and cheeses.
Simmer.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, stir together soup and cream cheese until smooth; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion and chili powder until tender.
Stir in chicken, green chilies and 2 tablespoons soup mixture.
Remove from heat.
In center of each tortilla, spread about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture.
Fold sides over filling; place, seam side down, in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Spread remaining soup mixture over enchiladas.
Cover with foil; bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 more minutes, until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: swedish butterhorns
directions: Cut butter and margarine into flour; add egg yolk and sour cream. Roll into a ball; wrap in wax paper. Chill at least 4 hours. Mix sugar, ground walnuts or pecans and cinnamon. Divide dough into 3 parts. Roll each portion of dough out separately (like a pie shell). Sprinkle with sugar mixture. Cut in wedges and roll up like a crescent roll. Bake on a slightly greased sheet at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. While warm, drizzle a powdered sugar glaze over the top.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Make 2 pies.

title: lettuce refrigerator salad
directions: Exact measurements aren't needed as you will see when you make the salad.
It can be made in any amount but is best for 4 or more servings.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: In medium saucepan, mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and drink mix.
Stir in water and oil.
Stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes until mixture forms a ball in center of pan.
Remove to floured surface and knead 1 minute.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container (margarine tub works well) in refrigerator.

title: corn bread dish
directions: Melt a stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, beat together the sour cream, eggs and corn muffin mix. Then add creamed corn and whole corn (drained).
Pour this mixture into the 9 x 13-inch pan with melted butter.
The butter will go to the sides, so stir the butter through the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover the first 3 ingredients with cold water and set overnight.
Next day, drain and wash.
Mix the vinegar, sugar and pickling spice together and pour over the cucumbers.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Lay cake mix on bottom of greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put cream cheese mixture on top; make sure mixture goes all around edges.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes in a 375° oven.
(Cake will rise to top and cream cheese will go to bottom.)
Cool; cut into squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix wheat germ, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Beat eggs until light colored and fluffy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and oil.
Stir in zucchini.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan for 1 hour; cool 10 minutes on rack.

title: twice-baked cheese potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes 1 to 1 1/4 hours until tender.
Cool just until easy to handle.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into halves; scoop out pulp, leaving thin shells.
Mash potato pulp and beans.

title: pully rolls
directions: Pour the water over the Spry and let cool.
Combine the yeast, sugar, salt and flour. Add the egg to water mixture.
Add flour mixture.
Chill overnight.
Two to 3 hours before using, break off small pieces of dough. Dip into the melted butter, cinnamon and sugar and nutmeats (if desired).
Let rise at room temperature until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 tea rings (jello molds).

title: party chicken(serves 8)
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in baking dish. Cover with cooked, cubed bacon. Scatter grated Cheddar cheese evenly over all.
Pour vermouth or wine over chicken. Top with grated Parmesan and black pepper. Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: 30 minute rolls
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well butter, yeast (dissolved in buttermilk), soda and sugar.
Make into dough; knead until smooth.
Roll out, cut, dip into butter and fold.
Let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: peach salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over softened cheese.
Mix well; fold in peaches and mix.
Fold in fruit cocktail and Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Stir butter and brown sugar; add egg.
Stir well.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Hand-mix well.
Add applesauce and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cream surprise(a cookout and buffet favorite)
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add bananas, pineapple and nuts. Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into an oiled 5 cup mold; Bundt pan is perfect.
Keep remaining 1/2 of mix at room temperature.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Remove mold and drop by spoonfuls the sour cream or whipped topping (careful not to spread too close to edges) onto frozen mixture.
Put back into freezer for 45 minutes. Remove and pour remaining mix on top.
Refrigerate until set. Double for large crowds.
Can also use sugar-free jello for this recipe.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil.
Saute meat and add hominy, tomato soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Let stand overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 30 to 45 more minutes.
Use Parmesan cheese on top.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Great with original or wheat Ritz crackers or vegetables.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° until bubbling.

title: new england recipe vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables in small amount of chicken broth.
Cook noodles.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese and crumbs. Top with cheese and crumbs.

title: italian vegetable casserole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in oil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, bay leaves, oregano, salt and garlic.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add grated cheese.
Place in small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until heated.
Add Mozzarella on top; place back in oven until cheese melts.

title: summer pie
directions: Fit pie crust into a 9-inch deep-dish tart pan; prick bottom and sides. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Remove and set aside.

title: quickie fudge
directions: Blend together confectioners sugar and cocoa in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour in milk.
Place butter on top.
Heat in Radarange oven on Full power for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir well to mix ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until blended.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes or in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Chill.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen pieces.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, add sugar and crushed crackers.
Mix well.
Add baking powder, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff. Bake in a lightly greased 6 x 10-inch pan for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or frozen yogurt. Delicious when served warm with ice cream and chocolate sauce (see recipe).
Serves 6.

title: golden glazed flank steak
directions: In small bowl combine soup mix, preserves and water; set aside.
In bottom of broiling pan, arrange steak and peppers; top with soup mixture.
Broil, turning once, until steak is done. Serve over hot rice.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend in mayonnaise and sugar, add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mary beth's pea salad
directions: Drain peas; mix with finely chopped onion, green pepper, celery and sweet pickles.
Mix and add sweet relish, hard-boiled eggs (chopped), mayonnaise, mustard and seasoning to taste.
If too dry, add more mayonnaise or sweet relish.

title: caviar appetizer
directions: Peel eggs and chop.
Combine eggs, salt and mayonnaise.
Pack in rounded bowl.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unmold on large plate. Lather sour cream all over unmolded egg mixture.
Gently spread caviar over all.
Decorate with sprigs of parsley.
Saltines around mold are for dipping.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt, pepper and pickle cubes and mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs and onion and mix lightly. Garnish with paprika.

title: jimmy carter's salad "for peanut butter lovers"
directions: Mix together the flour, stick margarine and peanuts.
Pat into 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; mix lightly until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Heat oil and butter in a large frying pan; add meatballs and saute, turning several times for 15 minutes or until evenly browned.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Add peanuts.
Microwave 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour on baking sheet and let stand for 30 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: apple nut torte
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie pan or square pan.
Preheat oven to 325°. Beat egg; sift dry ingredients into bowl, then add beaten egg, vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into wedges and serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Needs no liquid or shortening.
A small dessert, nice for two.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Melt 2 ounces of the butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the carrots and saute slowly until tender, about 25 minutes. Chop coarsely and place in a bowl. Increase heat to high and melt 1 ounce of the butter in the same skillet. Add the mushrooms and saute for 2 minutes. Chop coarsely and add to carrots; set aside. Melt 2 ounces butter over medium-high heat in the same skillet. Add the spinach and saute until wilted, about 2 minutes. Chop coarsely; place in a separate bowl and set aside. Line an 8 x 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil. Butter foil with the remaining butter. Beat together 4 eggs, the cheese, salt and pepper in a medium bowl. Add to the carrot mixture and mix well. Add the remaining eggs to the spinach and mix well. Spread half the carrot mixture over the bottom of the pan. Cover with the spinach mixture and top with the remaining carrot mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate. Preheat the oven to 400°. Remove the plastic wrap; cover the loaf pan loosely with foil and place in a roasting pan. Add enough boiling water to come halfway up the sides of the loaf pan.

title: baked cabbage jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Cover and bake in a 275° oven for two hours, stirring halfway through cooking.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt.
Melt butter in a baking dish; add corn mixture.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix eggs, bread and pineapple.
Add margarine and sugar.
Fold all ingredients.
Pour into casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ham.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt into a mixing bowl.
Add milk, 2 tablespoons oil and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.

title: jenny mayberry's success oriented
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Preheat large skillet over high heat until very hot.
Add oil and scrambled eggs.
Add rice and vegetables; stir and toss to blend quickly.
Add sesame oil, soy sauce and optional ingredients, if desired.

title: lemon rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in
rice,
salt,
butter and lemon juice.
Lower heat, cover, and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle
with
lemon rind before serving. Great with fish.
Serves 4.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Cook noodles separately.
Drain fruit and reserve juices.
Cook over low heat in saucepan the sugar, flour, eggs, salt and fruit juice until thick.
Add to noodles with drained fruit, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Make day ahead.

title: party dish burritos
directions: Prepare ground beef and burrito spices and seasonings according to package directions.
Warm tortillas according to directions.

title: cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Beat egg in large mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 1/2 minute.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool. (Can be served immediately.)
Wrap and refrigerate.
Twenty-five minutes before serving, heat oven to 375°.
Place wrapped cheese bread on oven rack.
Heat 15 minutes.
Slice.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let stand for a few minutes for oats to absorb moisture. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lorraine's coffee cake
directions: Mix together as pie crust 4 cups of the flour, the salt, 1 cup sugar and butter or margarine.
Add the remaining flour and blend. Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
After yeast works well, add to the warm milk.
Add all to the flour mixture; knead.
Let rise as usual.
This can be made into rolls or coffee cake.
If making coffee cake, after putting into pans, spread a thin coat of sour cream and some sugar on top.
After rising, bake at 375° until brown.
Add more sour cream; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and return to oven until it bubbles up.

title: hawaiian chicken salad(this is the best chicken salad!)
directions: Toss together the chicken, pineapple, dates and celery and refrigerate.
Add salad dressing just before serving.
We also add lettuce or napa.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In blender, mix onion and cheese, then add mayo.
Mix well. Add egg, then salt, pepper and parsley.
Blend.
Chill 15 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and let cool.
Add Cool Whip. Place nuts on top and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: marguerites
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients in order given.
Fill small buttered tins 2/3 full of mixture and place a nut meat on top of each.
Bake in moderate oven for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli elegante
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix flour into mayonnaise.
Then gradually blend in milk.
Stir in 1/3 cup of the cheese.
Saute bread crumbs in butter lightly.
Combine vegetables and mayonnaise in 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cocktail rye appetizer
directions: Mix together ingredients and spread on cocktail rye bread. Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle Hormel real bacon bits over top and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: rosemary roasted chicken(serves 6)
directions: Rinse the chicken and pat it dry.
Reserve the giblets and neck for another use.
Cut two 1-inch pieces of lemon peel from the lemon.
Cut the lemon in half and rub the chicken inside and out, squeezing the juice while you rub.
Salt and pepper the chicken lightly inside and out.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until thoroughly mixed.
Add the remaining ingredients all together and mix well.
Pour in unbaked crust and bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes.
Pie should be brown and look like it is well set, similar to pumpkin in solidity.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Make night before.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Lay bread down in dish. Put sausage over, then cheese and pour egg mixture over.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tropical bars
directions: Combine 3/4 cup butter, 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar; mix well and press into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Combine rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Spread filling over first layer while still hot.
Bake an additional 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs and powdered sugar until mixture is very light and fluffy and sugar is completely dissolved.
Stir in yogurt.
In a blender or food processor, process strawberries until pureed.
Add to egg mixture; stir to blend.
Add vanilla. Freeze mixture in an ice cream maker, or pour into a loaf pan or other mold and place in the freezer.
If using the freezer, stir mixture from time to time with a fork or small whisk to break up ice crystals and make it smooth.
Freezing time depends on size of mold.
One to 2 hours generally is enough.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, Dram Whip and ice cream until well blended. Pour into 2 pie crusts and freeze.
Eat and enjoy on hot summer day or any day.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients but shrimp in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake until shrimp are cooked, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges and French bread.
Serves 2 hungry people.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Grill chicken on both sides about 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients for sauce.
Baste generously on chicken, turning frequently, continuing to cook 15 to 20 minutes or until well glazed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Scald sour cream; stir in sugar, margarine and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Put water in large bowl; add yeast.
Blend in sour cream mixture; add eggs.
Blend in flour.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Grease pans.
Form into rolls on pan.
Let rise in warm place for 1 to 1 1/2 hours according to how warm it is.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: apple-walnut salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Peel and dice apples (leave skin on half an apple to add color).
Stir into mayonnaise.
Add celery and walnuts. Serve on salad greens and garnish with sliced oranges and grapes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 2 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When removed from oven, immediately place a Hershey Kiss on cookies.
Press in lightly.

title: phyllo cheese triangles
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Unfold phyllo and cover with a slightly damp towel to prevent pastry from drying out.
Place one sheet of phyllo on a flat surface; brush with butter.
Repeat with 2 more sheets of phyllo.
Cut lengthwise into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Place small amount of cheese mixture at base of each strip; fold the right bottom corner over to form a triangle. Continue folding back and forth into a triangle, gently pressing corners together.
Repeat procedure with remaining phyllo sheets, butter and cheese mixture.
Brush triangles with remaining butter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown.

title: pineapple breakfast rounds
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add pineapple and juice.
Mix well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Combine spinach, cheese, onions and soup.
Place in one-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan and stir in dressing mix.
Place on top of spinach mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the dry ingredients and stir them into the applesauce mixture just until smooth. Fold in the raisins and nuts.
Pour the batter into the loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean when inserted in the center.

title: mama's chocolate mint cake(three layers)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time), Hershey's syrup, self-rising flour and vanilla.
Bake on cookie sheet with high edges 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mayo biscuits
directions: Mix and fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dream bars
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and margarine until particles are fine (use low speed of mixer).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat 1 1/2 cups brown sugar with eggs until blended.
Mix in remaining ingredients and spread over partially baked crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
When cold cut into squares with sharp knife.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Prepare double pastry for 9-inch pie.
Mix all of the filling ingredients together, except the butter.
Put in pie shell and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: camp stew
directions: Cook chicken and beef until tender.
Cook potatoes and mash until in tiny pieces.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Should be cooked in large dishpan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts.
Stir until peanuts are light brown.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in baking soda and spread thinly on greased shallow pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: mom's sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole. Combine brown sugar, chopped pecans and flour. Sprinkle over sweet potatoes. Melt 1/2 cup margarine and pour over top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain and set aside.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations. Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle hash brown potatoes and Cheddar cheese over sausage.
Combine eggs, milk and salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake in additional 5 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump filling in pan.
Dump pineapple with juice.
Spread dry mix on top evenly.
Cut butter and place evenly on top.
Place nuts on top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: asparagus parmesan
directions: In skillet over medium heat, boil 1-inch of water. Add asparagus and 1 teaspoon salt; cover skillet and cook 5 minutes or until asparagus are tender-crisp. Drain.

title: pineapple glazed apple pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine 1 1/4 cups pineapple juice and sugar.
Bring to boiling; add apple wedges.
Simmer, covered, 3 to 4 minutes or until apples are tender, but not soft.
With slotted spoon, lift apples from pineapple liquid and set apples aside to drain.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in small amount of butter until tender.
Combine with shrimp and crabmeat.
Pour into prepared crust.
Sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and seasoning.
Pour over all; sprinkle top with basil.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 pint sherbet to the Jell-O-water mixture.
Stir well and add the can of pineapple with juice.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: cooked pimento and cheese
directions: Mix milk, salad dressing, vinegar and sugar in bowl and place in microwave or a double boiler.
Add cheese and melt, stirring occasionally. Add pimentos.

title: chocolate vanilla pecan dessert
directions: Combine flour and melted margarine.
Add nuts, press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before adding following layers:

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in carrots and pecans.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool for 1 hour.
Ice cake.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill. Makes enough to fill 8 dinner rolls.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff; mix in remaining ingredients and turn into a lightly greased 8-inch pie plate. Bake in a moderate oven until top is very firm, approximately 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with finely chopped pecans.

title: grapefruit punch
directions: Pour all ingredients in punch bowl; stir.
Add ice cubes just before serving.

title: pistachio cake
directions: 1. Grease tube or bundt pan and coat with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar (This mixture can be made to your
own taste).
2. Pour batter in and sprinkle remaining cinnamon mixture
on top of cake.
3. Bake in preheated 325° oven for approx 1 hour (Use
knife check).

title: gumdrop cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine shortening and sugars; beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until well combined.
Mix applesauce and soda and add to mixture.
Beat until well combined.
In another bowl, combine 1/2 cup flour with gumdrops, dates, nuts and raisins. Stir thoroughly until all ingredients are dusted with flour.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine remaining 3 1/2 cups flour with cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt.
Add to egg and sugar mixture; beat until smooth.
Stir in gumdrop mixture and vanilla.
Line 3 loaf pans with wax paper and distribute batter evenly.
Bake at 300° about 2 hours.
Cool on wire rack.
Remove from pan and peel off wax paper.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Cake is best stored for a week or two before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake layers and cool.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Refrigerate.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble.
Cook ground meat until not pink.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Combine beef, onion, catsup, salt and vinegar in 2 1/2-quart baking dish and pour little liquid off beans.
Add them to rest of ingredients. Stir to mix; sprinkle bacon over top and bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into the graham cracker crusts.
Chill 4 hours and serve.

title: special chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop.
Make a sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add soup, pimentos, almonds, broth and chicken.
Place in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake in oven until bubbly. Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: mildred lovett's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients, plus mushrooms; put in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes or potato chips, nuts and butter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 15.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes, remove from heat; add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and peanuts, if used.
Mix well.
Pour into greased or foil-lined pan.
Cool.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Boil and chop chicken breasts.
Place in casserole dish and top with blended soup and sour cream.
Crush enough Ritz crackers to cover chicken mixture and sprinkle with 1 T of poppy or sesame seeds.
Drizzle with melted oleo and bake at 300° for 40-45 minutes or until done.

title: sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir baking soda and vanilla into maple syrup; pour into shell.
Blend remaining ingredients with fingertips until mixture is crumbly, then spread over surface. Bake 30 minutes (may bubble over).
Let cool on rack; serve cold.

title: cherry pecan pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat butter and sugar with an electric mixer at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla, almond, salt and nutmeg.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour, one half cup at a time.
Beat until just blended.
Stir in cherries and pecans.
Spread batter evenly in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° until done, 60 to 70 minutes.

title: beef tidbits with pineapple
directions: Boil beef, onion, salt and pepper until tender.
Take juice and green pepper and cook until tender.
Put pineapple chunks and meat into liquid mixture.
Mix cornstarch with water to make smooth and stir into mixture until thick.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Combine 1/4 cup water, yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add to milk, water, egg and soft butter. Knead well, then let rise double in bulk.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
Heat water, brown sugar, shortening and 2 teaspoons salt until just warm, stirring constantly, until shortening just melts. Add to dry
mixture.
Beat on low for 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Stir in whole wheat flour and enough of remaining flour to make dough.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into ball.
Place in greased bowl; turn once.
Cover; let rise until double, 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; turn onto floured surface.
Divide in half. Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in two greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cover; let rise 1 1/4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
If top browns too quickly, cover with tent of foil for last 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and cinnamon together.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and butter in bowl until crumbly. Cover top of rhubarb in pan with crumb topping.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Sift flour.
Add all ingredients to creamed sugar.
Add flour and stir.
Line muffin tins with paper cups and spray with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. One muffin contains 20 calories.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook uncovered on medium heat.
Stir often.
Cook until it gets thick.

title: cheese french bread
directions: Cream oleo and mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients and spread on slices of bread.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it hairs from a spoon.
