Pour a little (about 1/2 cup) over well beaten egg whites, stirring constantly.
Return syrup to the stove and cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Pour off in whites and beat until sugary looking.
Add nuts and pour into buttered dish or pan.
Let cool.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and quarter. Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Shake potatoes, a few at a time, in bag to coat well.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place potatoes in single layer in pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once during baking. When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: swedish rosettes
directions: Beat eggs
slightly.
Add
sugar and salt.
Alternately add flour and
milk.

smooth.
Add
vanilla
and blend. Heat fat

Place	rosette

dip in batter (do not allow batter to cover top of iron). Immerse iron in hot fat completely for 25 to 30 seconds or until rosette
is

in

container. Will keep about 2 weeks.

title: pickle relish
directions: Put 1/2 cup salt in crock with ground cucumbers, onions and mangoes.
Let stand 2 hours.
Add alum and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over and simmer.
Can.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: apricot-glazed carrots
directions: Cook baby carrots and 1 teaspoon salt in boiling water, enough to cover carrots, in a large saucepan 15 to 20 minutes or until carrots are tender; drain. Melt butter in saucepan; stir in preserves until blended. Stir in remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, nutmeg, orange rind and orange juice. Cook 5 minutes. Add carrots. Gently toss to coat. Serves 4.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together raisins, dates, nuts, candied fruit, molasses and juice.
Cream together butter or oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, sugar and butter mixture into fruit mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Line 2 tube or loaf pans with aluminum foil; grease well.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Place shallow pan of water on lower shelf.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order given in an aluminum sheet pan.
Refrigerate at least 6 hour before serving.
Serves 10 or more.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla extract and salt; add milk.
Pour into six custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan filled 1-inch deep with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla extract, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° until done, about 1 hour.
Check often.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over combined sliced cucumbers and onions and let stand overnight.
The following day, drain real well.
Combine remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and pour hot over cucumber mixture.
Cool.
Put into 1 pint or 2 pint plastic containers and freeze.

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon color; add flour, baking powder, salt, cheese and butter.
Blend smoothly; stir in chilies. Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until brown and center is firm.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add spices, lemon flavoring and milk, blending well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to sugar mixture alternately with molasses to make a smooth dough.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick, cut with a cookie cutter and bake on greased and lightly floured cookie sheet about 8 minutes or until done.

title: baked flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle seasoning, salt and pepper on fish.
Place in baking pan. Spread onion over top.
Cover and bake 25 to 35 minutes. Serve with your choice of vegetables.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, butter, milk, spices and salt.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lentil roast
directions: Cook 1 cup lentils in 4 cups water for about 10 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid, if any.
Combine and mix thoroughly all other ingredients.
Add more bread crumbs if a drier loaf is desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with gravy or cranberry sauce.
Can cover with foil for 40 minutes and then uncover and bake 20 minutes so top of loaf gets browned.

title: salsa
directions: Heat oil
in
saucepan	over medium heat and add onion. Cook until tender.
Add jalapenos and stewed tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in garlic then add wine and simmer 10 minutes. Add other ingredients and cook about 1 1/2 hours on medium heat stirring occasionally.

title: buckeyes
directions: Knead together the first three ingredients.
Roll into one-inch balls and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Bring cola, cocoa, margarine and oil to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Mix in buttermilk, eggs and soda.
Fold in marshmallows.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry meat, onions and garlic salt until barely done.
Cook potatoes and carrots together until tender, then drain.
Put vegetables in baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over them.
Add heated cans of cream of mushroom soup and the water.
Put short crust over all and bake at about 400° until brown.
Serve.

title: best-ever oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, baking soda, and flour in small bowl and set aside.
Cream sugars, butter, vanilla and almond extract in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry mixture to butter/sugar mixture and stir together.
Add raisins if desired. Place dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool cookies slightly before removing them from the sheets.
Make about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix as any other pie.
Pour into unbaked pastry and cook in a medium oven about 45 minutes.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Add vanilla and food coloring.
Put in tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Mix soy sauce and paprika with buttermilk. Dip chicken in milk mixture, then roll in flour. Put small amount of cooking oil in large baking dish; arrange chicken in single layer, skin side down. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; turn and let other side brown. Thin sour cream with a little milk and pour over top of chicken. Bake 20 minutes more.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan and add onion and stir in flour to make thick paste.
Add evaporated milk, chicken broth and salt to taste.
Chop broccoli and add to liquid.
Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender.
Add mushrooms and cheese.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: turkey tortillas
directions: Crumble turkey in 1-quart casserole dish; add corn.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes, until turkey is no longer pink.

title: secret salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Fold in 1 cup crushed pineapple (drained) and 1 cup mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Crumble Bleu cheese into mixing bowl.
Add salad oil and mayonnaise and blend well.
Add sour cream.
Blend.
Add buttermilk, vinegar, salt and garlic powder.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add 2 cups of sugar and let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Cut
grapes
in
half.
Drain pineapple and add to grapes and
pecans.
Beat	cream;	add
vanilla and 1/3 cup of sugar. Drain liquid off cranberries.
Fold fruit mixture into cream.

title: sin city bars
directions: Mix cake mix with butter and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at
for
10 minutes.
Melt caramels in milk.
Pour over cooled
crust.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over melted caramels.
Bake
at
for
to 10 minutes until chocolate melts.
Cool
before
cutting.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Bars freeze well.

title: pineapple upside-down ham loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Combine sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Arrange pineapple on top of sugar mixture.
Pack meat on top of pineapple.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 375° oven.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.
You may substitute ham sausage for cooked ham.

title: peanut butter play dough(no cooking)
directions: Spoon out some big globs of peanut butter into a bowl.
Pour in a few spoonfuls of honey.
Add some powdered milk and start mixing with hands, adding more milk, until it makes a good dough. Playtime!!
Decorate as desired.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup Blue cheese.
Beat remaining Blue cheese and cream cheese on low speed.
Add mayonnaise and half and half; beat on medium speed until creamy.
Stir in reserved Blue cheese. Cover; refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep at least 1 week.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Place covered in refrigerator overnight. This is great served with pinto beans.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook sausage first in skillet until done.
Season ground beef with onion and garlic powder, pepper, seasoned salt and A.1. sauce.
Add seasoned ground beef to skillet with sausage.
Cook until ground beef is brown, drain.
Add Ragu sauce and tomatoes. Stir in skillet and simmer for half an hour on low heat.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and beaten eggs.
Cook until thickened and add vanilla and oleo.
This makes 2 pies.

title: pioneer vegetable soup
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Simmer in a covered kettle until all vegetables are tender.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Saute ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook beef; add bread crumbs, onion, eggs, oregano and salt. Steam a large cabbage head; place mixture in steamed leaves. Cover with sauce and foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Measure out 1/2 cup soup.
Combine with beef, breadcrumbs, onion, parsley and egg.
Shape into meatballs 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Brown in skillet with shortening.
Blend remaining soup with water.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: cornbread souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 11 x 7 x 2 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 8-layer salad
directions: Layer as follows:
Tear lettuce in small pieces and put in 3-quart oblong dish.
Add celery, pepper, onion and peas.
Spread thin layer of salad dressing over all.
Then spread balance of salad dressing.
Top with sugar, then grated cheese.
Finish with bacon bits.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serves at least 12 people.

title: tangy homemade chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until cooked and tender.
Cut up chicken in small pieces in a medium size bowl.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper, and sweet pickles, stirring frequently to mix.
Add pickle juice, sandwich relish and Dukes mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: bass fish stew
directions: Can use rockfish, catfish or flounder.

title: orange cranberry bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and soda. Combine egg, orange peel, orange juice and salad oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir well until mixed.
Fold in nuts and berries. Bake in greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches) at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers
and
cut off stems.
Slice and pack in salt brine
solution,
with
enough salt to float an egg.
It takes about
quarts of water.	A churn is good to pack them in. Cover and let stand 7 days.
Wash cucumbers and churn and repack in	alum
and
enough
water to cover.
Let stand for 6 hours. Rinse
cucumbers and wash churn, repack in vinegar and let	stand 6 hours.
Drain vinegar off; don't wash.
Pack the pickles,
a layer of cucumbers, a layer of sugar.
Add spices; I tie
my spices
in a cheese cloth.	Add a little vinegar to taste.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until soft ball forms.
Add butter. Mix in popcorn.
Butter hands and form 3-inch balls.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Saute onion in butter.
Blend soup and milk together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma rau's bona salat(bean salad)
directions: Cook green beans until stick-tender, not mushy.
Fry bacon until slightly brown; add onions and saute.
Drain fat and add to beans.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Pour hot mixture over beans.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve warm.

title: angel wings
directions: Cut butter into flour.
In a separate bowl, combine egg yolks, salt and rum. Combine.
Knead dough on a floured board. This can also be done in a bread machine or pasta maker.
Let the dough set in a bowl for about 30 minutes.
Roll out a small about of dough, about 1/8 inch thick.
The thinner the dough the better. Cut into strips about 1 X 4 inches long.
Pull one end through the slit.
Fry in hot oil a few at a time.
Drain.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar, then add peanut butter and mix well.
Fold in 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Add remaining Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate pie.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and chop onion; boil 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soups, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
Add half of stuffing mix and 1/4 cup of melted oleo.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top and pour other 1/4 cup melted oleo over top. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stir-fried liver
directions: Slice liver thin and mix with cornstarch and crushed garlic. Brown quickly in hot oil.
Add finely sliced onion and mushrooms. Stir-fry until meat is evenly browned, then add chopped scallions and soy sauce.
Continue cooking with constant stirring for 6 to 9 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Mix with rhubarb.
Put in an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake until rhubarb is done (approximately 45 minutes).
May top with meringue.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour nuts in the bottom. Combine butter, brown sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour and salt.
Spoon over nuts.
Sprinkle candied fruits over top and press into top of batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool before cutting.

title: ginger cheese dressing
directions: Blend the cottage cheese, skim milk, lemon or lime juice, honey and ginger in a blender until smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Fifteen minutes before baking, place rack in center of oven and preheat to 375°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners.
To make the muffins, in a food processor, process the flour, sugar, butter, buttermilk, walnuts, eggs, maple flavoring, baking powder and salt for 3 seconds.

Run a spatula around the sides of the work bowl; then pulse once or twice, just enough to combine. Leave the batter in the bowl and carefully remove the metal blade. Insert the all-purpose (4 mm) slicer.
Slice the cranberries into the batter.
Remove the slicer and fold them in with a spatula.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Place each frozen loaf on a cookie sheet alone, greased and covered as per package instructions.
Let rise.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and cold water.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let set slightly.
Add pineapple, sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Let set and get firm in refrigerator.
Mix pineapple juice, flour, egg and sugar.
Cook until
thick. Add cream cheese and let cool.
Prepare the Dream Whip. Fold into mixture. Spread over chilled jello. Refrigerate.

title: dumplings in syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop in hot syrup.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; add onions, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender; add salt, chili powder, sugar and flour; stir.
Add tomato juice and catsup; stir.
Simmer 1 hour; add cooked beans. Cook on low for 1 to 2 hours.
This will freeze well for later use.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and the vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: apple dressing
directions: In a shallow baking pan, toast bread crumbs in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, 2 soup cans of water and chopped green olives.
Mix; stir in raw rice.
Salt and pepper fryer.
Place in pan; cover with foil and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake about 10 minutes to brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and place in a casserole dish.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix together milk, water and vanilla pudding.
Chill 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip.
Place vanilla wafers in dish; add bananas, then the mix.

title: irene's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease casserole dish and pour in 1/2 cup water.
Shape into loaf.
Place in dish and cook almost an hour at 350°.
When almost done, spread catsup on top of meat loaf.
Better when really brown.

title: sourdough blueberry muffins
directions: Blend soda, sugar and spices together.
Mix all other ingredients in a separate bowl with the cup of sourdough starter. Add soda mixture and mix until just moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated turkey fillets
directions: Rinse turkey fillets and pat dry.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into rectangular enamel or ovenproof glass baking dish.
Add fillets, turning to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight, turning fillets several times.
Grill or broil marinated fillets. Serve hot.
This dish is also good chilled and sliced over salad greens.
(Keep covered in the refrigerator.)
Serves 6.

title: jam thumbprints
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Gradually add flour, mixing well. Shape into 3/4-inch balls; dip in 2 slightly beaten egg whites, then roll in finely chopped walnuts lightly covering ball.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press down center of each ball with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Let cool, then add cherry or strawberry preserves in center.

title: cherry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar
well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour. Stir in vanilla.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 3/4 of the batter in pan. Drop pie filling by teaspoonfuls, then drop remaining batter over filling by spoonfuls.
Bake for about 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 325°.
Add paprika on top before serving.
May also add a little butter.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a large bowl; glass is pretty.
Layer in this order: spinach, sprinkle with salt, pepper and a little sugar; bacon; eggs; iceberg lettuce, sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar; Spanish onions and peas.
Cover with a mixture of mayonnaise and Miracle Whip (or use all mayonnaise).
Spread shredded cheese on top.
Do not toss.
Should stand 6 to 8 hours, but best if served within 18 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and peel cukes; slice.
Add sliced onion and green pepper.
Combine 2 cups sugar, 1 cup vinegar, 1 tablespoon celery salt and 1 teaspoon salt; let set 30 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and set in refrigerator.

title: peach crisp dessert
directions: Put peaches
and juice into a 9 x 3-inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle
dry
cake
mix
evenly
on
top of peaches.
Drizzle melted margarine on top of cake mix.
If desired top with nuts and/or coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot dog supreme
directions: In large skillet, empty large can tomatoes; cut hot dogs thin like a dime.
Place over the tomatoes; let simmer until all juice is gone; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.
Costs less than $3.00.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: * One can (16 ounces) peeled tomatoes can be substituted for the 3 large tomatoes.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Layer meat in casserole.
Mix soups and sour cream; pour over meat.
Mix stuffing with broth or water and melted margarine. Place over meat and soups in casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Put chocolate chips in double boiler on low until melted. Add peanut butter and keep warm.
Cream oleo and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add pecans.
Spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust tests done.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on top and bake 3 more minutes.
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies to chocolate and peanut butter mixture and spread on top of cooled bars.
Chill, cut into bars and store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Put ingredients in a heavy Dutch oven or large casserole.
Add large chunks of potato, carrots, celery, a small head of cabbage and several small onions. Mix together thoroughly and cover tightly. Bake 4 hours at 325°. Do not peek!

title: grill barbecued chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Place chicken parts in deep glass bowl, then pour marinade over to completely cover chicken.
Marinate overnight. Cook on grill while basting with marinade, about 1 hour cooking time.
Do not use any leftover marinade.

title: bishops apples
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
Mix together other ingredients. Pour over apples in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Baste every now and then.
Serve warm or cold with ham, pork roast or chops or barbecue.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cut apricots into quarters and place in saucepan with water.
Simmer until tender; cool.
Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flour, soda, cooled apricots.
Sprinkle cherries, almonds and raisins with flour and add.
Spoon batter into 2 large or 4 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in 275° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or 1 1/4 hours for small pans. Cool in pans on rack and pour 2 Tbsp. rum over each loaf while still warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, celery and onion together in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and add remaining ingredients (save crumbs for top).
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: cooked mayonnaise
directions: Combine in saucepan flour, sugar, and salt.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and pour into blender, add eggs, blending in oil slowly. Chill before using.

title: moma's pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time,
mixing
well after each one; sift dry ingredients together 3
times.
Add
to egg mixture alternately with milk. Mix well after
each
addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan in oven preheated
to 325° for 1 hour or until it springs back when touched.

title: strawberry-melon salad
directions: Cut melons in half and remove seeds.
Use a melon shell with leaf lettuce.
Divide melon balls among lined shells.
Mound a generous 1/3 cup cottage cheese in center of each.
Place 1/4 cup strawberries around each mound.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients and pour into pastry shell. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart (or slightly larger) microwave safe bowl, mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook four minutes in microwave.
Stir and cook an additional four minutes.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Blend and cook two more minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and spread very thin.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces. (Entire cooking time is 10 minutes.)

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Grate the rind fine in a bowl.
Add sugar, flour, egg yolks and butter and mix.
If hard to mix, add a little lemon juice to soften.
Add the rest of the lemon juice, then the milk and egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 400° for 25 minutes more.
Makes 1 pie.

title: easy chocolate truffles
directions: Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Gradually add sugar until well blended.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins about 15 to 20 minutes. Skin the hot potatoes and dice. Toss the sugar and vinegar with the warm potatoes. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate. Can garnish with green pepper rings and/or paprika, radishes or parsley. Best if made the day before serving. Serves 15.
Must do ahead.

title: busy day beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 7 hours.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Melt bark.
Add chocolate chips and peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions together.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Repeat for 10 minutes and drain well.
Add sugar, spice and vinegar; cook 15 minutes and can in hot jars.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Dice pepper and shred carrot.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper and add to vegetables. Toss lightly and refrigerate.

title: four layer delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix margarine, flour and cream; spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove cabbage leaves carefully; wilt in hot water.
Blend beef, rice, butter, tomato sauce, salt, red pepper and cinnamon. Place about 2 tablespoons of beef mixture in each leaf; roll up firmly and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Arrange cabbage rolls close together in pan; cover with tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 1 hour and 10 minutes or until beef is done.
Could be baked also in covered casserole.

title: bacon-water chestnuts hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar, pimentos, salt and pepper together and boil for 5 minutes to make sauce.
Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Make a paste.
Add to sauce, stirring until thick and clear.
Wrap 1/2 water chestnut with 1/3 slice bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake or broil until bacon is done, turning as necessary.
Dip bacon in sauce.
All this may be made and frozen. (Do not bake the bacon before freezing.)

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Peel and clean the shrimp.
Combine all other ingredients in a small bowl.
Place shrimp in a large glass bowl.
Pour marinade over shrimp and refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
Soak bamboo skewers in water.
Place shrimp on skewers and grill the shrimp 2 minutes on each side, just until they curl and turn pink, brushing with the marinade.
Serves 6.

title: sugar free oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In a small pan, mix the honey and the brown sugar.
Heat until boiling point and continue mixing.
Add the butter, peanut butter and vanilla and mix well.

title: chicken stratum(a fix ahead casserole)
directions: Pour over top of casserole.
Bake in 325°
oven for about 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt, pepper, chopped onion, chopped bell pepper, rolled oats and milk.
Mix well.
Add beef and pork.
The secret of a meat loaf is to have it very moist, hardly holds together in pan.
Shape meat into a loaf.
Bake in a heavy pan. Small amount of water (1 cup) around the meat loaf.
Baste several times during cooking period.
Bake in 375° oven for one hour or more, if needed.

title: * apricot-cheese salad *
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add juice and drained fruits.
Fold in marshmallows.
Chill until set.

title: west virginia baked beans
directions: Brown and drain beef; mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mini sour cream biscuits
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients. Drop by a round tablespoonful into greased miniature muffin tin. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 1 dozen.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and mix in sugar, oil, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix thoroughly with zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Put in cold oven and turn to 325° (no preheat). Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bread tests done with toothpick.
Cool in pans.

title: steamed chicken\(electric skillet version)
directions: Flour chicken and place in the skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Cook with cover on for 45 minutes at 350° or until tender and brown.

title: chex party mix(easy as 1, 2, 3)
directions: In bowl, mix salt and Lea & Perrins with melted butter; mix well.
Put together other ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Pour butter mixture over cereal in bag; shake well.
Pour into large bowl and microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer the Stove Top stuffing first, then the chicken.
Next mix soup with broth and pour over stuffing and chicken.
Crumble the crackers over mixture, then pour melted butter over the crackers.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate.

title: apple juice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 1/2 of mixture in blender and blend well.
Add the rest of mixture and blend.

title: wanda's wonder cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart bowl.
Add pie filling.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and flour together.
Add egg; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: chinese salad
directions: Saute the noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds in oil until lightly brown.
Don't mix together until ready to eat.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake according to directions on box in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. While hot, punch holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake and then pour cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool, cover with Cool Whip.
Then cover with can of coconut.
Let it stand overnight.

title: russian tea cake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure and sift flour and salt together.
Blend in.
Mix in nuts and chill dough.

title: oatmeal orange muffins
directions: Soak oats in water and juice for 15 minutes.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add oats and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In Dutch oven combine all ingredients except flour and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through (15 to 20 minutes).
In small bowl, stir together flour and butter; stir into hot soup.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until thickened, 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 4 hours in a 250° oven.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together lemon cake mix, egg and oil.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Save 1 cup for topping.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese, lemon juice and egg.
Spread over crust.
Top with 1 cup left from crust.
Bake 15 more minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate and cut into small bars.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: german apple cake
directions: In small bowl, mix 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together. In large bowl, mix all other ingredients, except apples.
Batter will be thick.
Grease tube pan.
Cover bottom of pan with batter. Add a layer of apples; sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture. Repeat this twice more.
(There will be 3 layers of apples.)
End with a thin layer of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut up cabbage; cook on top of stove with a little warm water. Mix hamburg, salt, pepper, onion and rice together with a little warm water.
Rinse and top peppers.
Stuff with hamburg mixture. Cook until hamburg is almost done.
Put tomato paste on top of peppers and cook until peppers are soft.
Put in fridge overnight. Serve next day.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Debone and take skin off boiled chicken.
Break up into small pieces.
Set aside.

Boil spaghetti in 1 cup broth and other water. Saute onions, pepper and celery in butter until soft and clear. Combine 1 cup broth, Ro-Tel, cream of chicken soup, 1/2 pound Velveeta and simmer on stove.
Add onions, peppers, celery, chicken and cooked spaghetti to mixture.
Once mixed, pour into casserole dish and top with other half of Velveeta.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: 1-2-3-4 yellow cake batter
directions: Cream
shortening.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add well beaten egg yolks.	Then add flour that has been sifted 3 times with
salt and baking powder along with milk (a little of each at
a
time). Last,
fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 square layers.
Also, this recipe is used for cupcakes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple and heat to boiling. Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Add cream cheese and let stand for five minutes.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: good cheese spread
directions: Slowly melt butter and Velveeta together.
Mix in pimentos. Beat eggs well and add to mixture, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise and cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat and prepare noodles according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with garlic and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with 6 tortillas.
Add meat on top.
Cover with remaining 6 tortillas.
Spread chicken soup over these.
Pour milk over soup. Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
A very easy and tasty dish!

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Add vinegar and eggs.
Add pecans and raisins.
Bake at 400° in 2 pie shells for about 10 minutes.
Then turn to 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
To prevent pies from browning too fast, place pan of water on top rack.
